1
00:00:15,015 --> 00:00:19,152
A makeover project
for your most unhinged leftovers.

2
00:00:19,219 --> 00:00:23,023
The best chefs in Korea will
turn your fridge inside out.

3
00:00:23,089 --> 00:00:24,858
The classy cooking talk show has returned.

4
00:00:24,924 --> 00:00:27,560
-<i>Chef & My Fridge</i>!
-<i>My Fridge</i>!

5
00:00:30,997 --> 00:00:33,566
We present the best chefs in Korea

6
00:00:33,633 --> 00:00:36,803
who will turn your fridge inside out!

7
00:00:36,870 --> 00:00:38,671
-Welcome.
-Welcome.

8
00:00:38,738 --> 00:00:43,143
Last time, we had a battle between
the returning chefs and the new chefs,

9
00:00:43,209 --> 00:00:45,812
and the new chefs lost completely
by three to one.

10
00:00:45,879 --> 00:00:50,817
Only Chef Park Eun-yeong
barely managed to save face.

11
00:00:50,884 --> 00:00:52,952
Gosh, Choi Kang-rok was defeated.

12
00:00:53,019 --> 00:00:54,154
(CRIES…)

13
00:00:54,220 --> 00:00:55,355
My gosh. Right?

14
00:00:55,422 --> 00:01:00,193
So, the chefs of <i>Culinary Class Wars</i> will
challenge them once again.

15
00:01:00,260 --> 00:01:03,696
The returning chefs of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>
versus the new chefs.

16
00:01:03,763 --> 00:01:07,200
-They challenged them to get revenge.
-Who could it be this time?

17
00:01:07,267 --> 00:01:10,070
Come to think of it, Chef Hyun-suk
kept going on about <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>

18
00:01:10,136 --> 00:01:12,005
and ended up switching sides.

19
00:01:12,072 --> 00:01:13,573
-Yes, Chef Hyun-suk.
-He was

20
00:01:13,640 --> 00:01:15,241
-supposed to be here.
-Yes.

21
00:01:15,308 --> 00:01:18,178
He was one of the returning chefs,
but he's with <i>Culinary Class Wars</i> now.

22
00:01:18,244 --> 00:01:19,412
CHOI HYUN-SUK SWITCHES OVER

23
00:01:19,479 --> 00:01:22,582
-Well, he was on the show.
-Yes, I guess it's true.

24
00:01:22,649 --> 00:01:23,983
Are you challenging them today?

25
00:01:24,050 --> 00:01:26,419
As I mentioned last time,

26
00:01:26,486 --> 00:01:28,955
I'm done salting food
with my signature move,

27
00:01:29,022 --> 00:01:30,757
acting funny, and showing off.

28
00:01:30,824 --> 00:01:32,158
So today,

29
00:01:32,225 --> 00:01:34,727
I want to join Team Culinary Class Wars…

30
00:01:34,794 --> 00:01:36,396
Why did you laugh? You can't do that.

31
00:01:36,463 --> 00:01:37,997
You said you were done being funny,

32
00:01:38,064 --> 00:01:40,500
-I see.
-That's the sly technician.

33
00:01:40,567 --> 00:01:41,668
I see.

34
00:01:41,734 --> 00:01:47,474
This week and next week, Chef Hyun-suk
will be with the challenging chefs.

35
00:01:47,540 --> 00:01:49,309
If you take a good look,

36
00:01:49,375 --> 00:01:52,812
you'll notice that
you're both missing one person.

37
00:01:52,879 --> 00:01:58,718
Both teams will each get to play
with one new chef as a secret weapon.

38
00:01:58,785 --> 00:02:01,754
-Who could it be?
-Which chefs would show up and join us…

39
00:02:01,821 --> 00:02:02,689
-…here today?
-I wonder.

40
00:02:02,755 --> 00:02:05,592
These are the best chefs
for this return match.

41
00:02:05,658 --> 00:02:06,493
Come on out!

42
00:02:06,559 --> 00:02:08,995
Who are the two chefs?

43
00:02:09,729 --> 00:02:11,397
-I'm so curious.
-Gosh.

44
00:02:11,464 --> 00:02:13,433
The new chefs!

45
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:15,235
WHO ARE THE TWO ACE CHEFS?

46
00:02:18,872 --> 00:02:23,109
Please welcome
the two prominent Italian chefs in Korea!

47
00:02:23,610 --> 00:02:24,644
The winner is Kwon Sung-jun!

48
00:02:24,711 --> 00:02:25,979
BLACK SPOON, KWON SUNG-JUN, WINS

49
00:02:26,846 --> 00:02:29,182
I was always confident
about making risotto.

50
00:02:29,249 --> 00:02:31,651
Actually, there's nothing
I'm not confident about.

51
00:02:31,718 --> 00:02:34,654
I think I could win against most people.

52
00:02:35,221 --> 00:02:37,323
I'm the flavor mafia from Naples.

53
00:02:38,424 --> 00:02:40,026
A SAINT WHO SMILES WHEN HE'S TEASED

54
00:02:40,093 --> 00:02:41,327
AND EVEN WHEN HE'S DISTURBED

55
00:02:41,394 --> 00:02:42,962
He's the original star Italian chef.

56
00:02:43,029 --> 00:02:46,399
The return of the saint, Chef Sam Kim.

57
00:02:46,466 --> 00:02:49,269
Did you choose not to participate
in <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>?

58
00:02:49,335 --> 00:02:51,104
No, I…

59
00:02:51,171 --> 00:02:52,939
They had to have contacted you.

60
00:02:53,006 --> 00:02:54,140
I was busy.

61
00:02:54,207 --> 00:02:55,275
You were busy?

62
00:02:55,341 --> 00:02:56,543
I knew it.

63
00:02:56,609 --> 00:02:59,612
Wait, why do you treat Sam like this?

64
00:02:59,679 --> 00:03:00,914
-Why?
-When he said he was busy,

65
00:03:00,980 --> 00:03:03,316
you'd usually go,
"Do you think they're free?"

66
00:03:03,383 --> 00:03:05,785
-That's the <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> style.
-Right.

67
00:03:05,852 --> 00:03:08,254
Why do you attack me and not him?

68
00:03:08,321 --> 00:03:10,590
-It's his first day.
-It's his first time here.

69
00:03:10,657 --> 00:03:12,725
-It's his day one.
-I can't attack him immediately.

70
00:03:12,792 --> 00:03:15,128
-I was also busy, but I was on the show.
-I know.

71
00:03:15,195 --> 00:03:18,298
All right.
We'll start devouring him in 30 minutes.

72
00:03:18,364 --> 00:03:19,832
Really?

73
00:03:19,899 --> 00:03:22,035
-We have to let him cook first.
-Exactly.

74
00:03:22,101 --> 00:03:24,103
He's still like raw fish.

75
00:03:24,170 --> 00:03:26,573
-Now, this next chef.
-Yes.

76
00:03:26,639 --> 00:03:29,042
He's the chef who surpassed
all other talented chefs.

77
00:03:29,108 --> 00:03:30,810
He obviously surpassed Hyun-suk.

78
00:03:30,877 --> 00:03:33,646
-Hyun-suk? Yes.
-He did.

79
00:03:33,713 --> 00:03:37,450
The winner of <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>,
known as Napoli Matfia, Kwon Sung-jun!

80
00:03:37,517 --> 00:03:39,152
All right! Kwon Sung-jun!

81
00:03:39,219 --> 00:03:41,788
WELCOME TO THE SHOW

82
00:03:41,854 --> 00:03:43,323
The winner!

83
00:03:43,389 --> 00:03:45,391
He destroyed 100 chefs.

84
00:03:45,458 --> 00:03:46,459
He did.

85
00:03:46,526 --> 00:03:51,731
To be frank,
I heard Team Culinary Class Wars

86
00:03:51,798 --> 00:03:53,633
didn't do so well.

87
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:56,002
-No.
-Not their first time.

88
00:03:56,069 --> 00:03:58,204
They won against one of them,

89
00:03:58,271 --> 00:04:01,374
and the opponent was
the webtoon artist, Kim Poong.

90
00:04:01,441 --> 00:04:02,575
Yes, one win against Poong.

91
00:04:02,642 --> 00:04:04,177
We practically lost everything.

92
00:04:05,011 --> 00:04:06,112
THE WINNER SUDDENLY PICKS A FIGHT

93
00:04:06,179 --> 00:04:08,414
-You saw right through it all.
-What?

94
00:04:08,481 --> 00:04:10,516
-What are you talking about?
-I couldn't take it.

95
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:13,486
The first round doesn't count
because the winner wasn't there.

96
00:04:14,921 --> 00:04:16,889
-But you get 15 minutes.
-That's the problem.

97
00:04:16,956 --> 00:04:18,091
Can you do this in 15 minutes?

98
00:04:18,157 --> 00:04:19,993
Actually, in a way, I can say

99
00:04:20,627 --> 00:04:21,527
I don't think I can lose.

100
00:04:21,594 --> 00:04:24,497
-He doesn't think he can lose.
-He doesn't think he can lose.

101
00:04:24,564 --> 00:04:26,866
I think he's the Hyun-suk type.

102
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:28,468
-They seem similar.
-No, no.

103
00:04:28,534 --> 00:04:29,369
We're a bit different.

104
00:04:29,435 --> 00:04:33,306
He's very confident and talented,

105
00:04:33,373 --> 00:04:35,675
but at times, his words are

106
00:04:35,742 --> 00:04:38,177
a little too bold

107
00:04:38,244 --> 00:04:41,047
-and lacking in social skills…
-What?

108
00:04:41,114 --> 00:04:43,816
-Lacking in social skills?
-That's why I think you two are alike.

109
00:04:43,883 --> 00:04:46,319
-This can be controversial.
-Our tones are a bit different.

110
00:04:46,386 --> 00:04:49,289
Then, you are completely different
from Chef Kang-rok.

111
00:04:49,355 --> 00:04:51,424
-Overall, yes.
-It's as if he's stuck in the middle.

112
00:04:51,991 --> 00:04:55,295
Even his chair looks too low.
Can someone bring him a higher chair?

113
00:04:55,361 --> 00:04:58,531
-He looks too low.
-Yes, the chair seems sunken.

114
00:04:59,666 --> 00:05:01,434
Does it feel reassuring to have him?

115
00:05:03,670 --> 00:05:05,171
He won't be cooking in my place, so…

116
00:05:05,238 --> 00:05:06,439
Well, that's true.

117
00:05:07,373 --> 00:05:09,509
-My gosh.
-That's true. He won't replace you.

118
00:05:09,575 --> 00:05:11,611
-That's a great answer.
-He's right.

119
00:05:11,678 --> 00:05:14,180
-It's reassuring to have him on the team.
-I see, on the team.

120
00:05:14,247 --> 00:05:16,215
Do you have a piece of advice for him?

121
00:05:17,283 --> 00:05:19,986
This universe won't be easy.

122
00:05:21,954 --> 00:05:26,259
And now, let us present the fridge owners

123
00:05:26,326 --> 00:05:28,828
who visited us with their fridges today.

124
00:05:28,895 --> 00:05:32,665
I was in huge shock when I heard the names

125
00:05:32,732 --> 00:05:34,701
of these fridge owners.

126
00:05:34,767 --> 00:05:36,469
-Who could it be?
-Yes, I did.

127
00:05:36,536 --> 00:05:39,405
I thought,
"These two came with their fridges?"

128
00:05:39,472 --> 00:05:43,576
These are actors
you rarely see on a variety show.

129
00:05:43,643 --> 00:05:46,012
Please welcome today's fridge owners!

130
00:05:46,079 --> 00:05:47,714
Come on out!

131
00:05:49,382 --> 00:05:50,683
Who could it be?

132
00:05:51,351 --> 00:05:54,053
-These are today's fridge owners.
-What?

133
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:55,154
PRESENTING THE FRIDGE OWNERS

134
00:05:55,888 --> 00:05:58,091
The actors who always deliver,

135
00:05:58,157 --> 00:06:00,426
Please welcome
Lee Hee-jun and Song Joong-ki!

136
00:06:00,493 --> 00:06:02,962
People would think I died mid-coitus
if I died now!

137
00:06:03,029 --> 00:06:05,932
He's an actor who has
brutally excellent acting skills.

138
00:06:05,998 --> 00:06:07,700
He can play a cheeky romantic guy

139
00:06:07,767 --> 00:06:09,502
to a heinous villain.

140
00:06:09,569 --> 00:06:12,572
An actor with a thousand faces,
Lee Hee-jun!

141
00:06:12,638 --> 00:06:13,973
-Welcome.
-Hello.

142
00:06:15,141 --> 00:06:15,975
Hello.

143
00:06:16,042 --> 00:06:18,211
I can't believe I get to present this man.

144
00:06:18,277 --> 00:06:19,812
I plan to buy Soonyang.

145
00:06:19,879 --> 00:06:23,349
From the youngest son of a conglomerate
to a mafia boss,

146
00:06:23,416 --> 00:06:25,952
he always shows extraordinary
transformations in every work.

147
00:06:26,018 --> 00:06:28,921
An actor who works constantly
and is called as diligent as a cow,

148
00:06:28,988 --> 00:06:31,424
a very dear actor to all of us,
Song Joong-ki!

149
00:06:31,491 --> 00:06:33,459
-It's great to have you!
-It's nice to see you.

150
00:06:33,526 --> 00:06:35,795
WELCOME TO THE SHOW

151
00:06:35,862 --> 00:06:38,164
Joong-ki, we haven't seen you
on variety shows for a while.

152
00:06:38,231 --> 00:06:40,833
I guess so. A long time ago,

153
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:44,637
-I was a regular member of <i>Running Man</i>.
-Right.

154
00:06:44,704 --> 00:06:46,038
It's my first time since then.

155
00:06:46,105 --> 00:06:47,607
-I see.
-It's been a while, then.

156
00:06:47,673 --> 00:06:50,176
-It's been ten years.
-Ten years?

157
00:06:50,243 --> 00:06:52,979
By any chance, do you know these chefs?

158
00:06:53,045 --> 00:06:55,982
Yes, I'm a huge fan of them.

159
00:06:56,048 --> 00:07:00,219
Which one of the eight chefs
did you want to meet the most?

160
00:07:00,286 --> 00:07:02,488
Well, first, Chef Choi Hyun-suk.

161
00:07:02,555 --> 00:07:06,726
I thought he was really cool
when he showed his professional demeanor

162
00:07:06,793 --> 00:07:09,328
when he was on <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.

163
00:07:09,395 --> 00:07:13,499
I also want to try Dongpo pork
made by Chef Eun-yeong

164
00:07:13,566 --> 00:07:15,435
and Chef Yeon-bok.

165
00:07:15,501 --> 00:07:17,303
BIG SMILES

166
00:07:17,370 --> 00:07:19,539
I've never ordered a dish like that,

167
00:07:20,306 --> 00:07:21,674
but I did after watching it.

168
00:07:21,741 --> 00:07:23,643
However, it was really bad.

169
00:07:23,709 --> 00:07:25,278
SOMBER VIBES…

170
00:07:25,344 --> 00:07:29,649
I'm so curious about the taste
of Dongpo pork when it's actually good.

171
00:07:29,715 --> 00:07:32,985
Joong-ki, did you have a chef
you wanted to meet in person?

172
00:07:33,052 --> 00:07:35,922
-I wanted to meet everyone here.
-I see.

173
00:07:35,988 --> 00:07:38,357
-But if I had to pick one…
-Yes?

174
00:07:38,424 --> 00:07:41,861
I really wanted to meet

175
00:07:41,928 --> 00:07:43,830
Napoli Matfia, Chef Sung-jun.

176
00:07:43,896 --> 00:07:49,302
My wife had lived in Italy all her life,
so I live there for half of the year.

177
00:07:49,368 --> 00:07:50,369
Right.

178
00:07:50,436 --> 00:07:53,239
I was already into Italian cuisine,

179
00:07:53,306 --> 00:07:57,510
then I watched Chef Sung-jun
winning the <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.

180
00:07:57,577 --> 00:08:01,814
I still remember how he did this
with the risotto. Is it called tossing?

181
00:08:01,881 --> 00:08:04,116
-Doing this?
-Really quickly.

182
00:08:04,684 --> 00:08:06,619
I'm too nervous to look at him.

183
00:08:07,653 --> 00:08:08,488
FEELING SHY

184
00:08:08,554 --> 00:08:10,623
A celebrity for Joong-ki.

185
00:08:11,424 --> 00:08:12,325
BOTH FEELING SHY

186
00:08:12,391 --> 00:08:14,126
That's Chef Sung-jun.

187
00:08:14,193 --> 00:08:17,497
-It's not easy to have them here at once.
-No.

188
00:08:17,563 --> 00:08:22,969
I'm sure you have a reason
for visiting <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> together.

189
00:08:23,035 --> 00:08:26,105
-We filmed a movie together.
-I see.

190
00:08:26,172 --> 00:08:29,509
It's called <i>Bogota</i>,
and it premieres on December 31st.

191
00:08:29,575 --> 00:08:32,678
-It premieres on the last day of the year.
-That's right.

192
00:08:32,745 --> 00:08:35,047
The character I play is named Guk-hee.

193
00:08:35,114 --> 00:08:37,483
Right after the IMF crisis,

194
00:08:37,550 --> 00:08:40,253
Guk-hee's family lose all hope

195
00:08:40,319 --> 00:08:44,156
<i>and almost flees to Colombia,</i>
<i>the other side of the world.</i>

196
00:08:44,223 --> 00:08:46,559
<i>The family attempts to settle there.</i>

197
00:08:47,126 --> 00:08:48,227
You can call me bro from now on.

198
00:08:49,061 --> 00:08:50,363
I know. You're different.

199
00:08:50,429 --> 00:08:51,731
You will be tested.

200
00:08:52,565 --> 00:08:54,000
This was Soo-yeong's plan.

201
00:08:54,066 --> 00:08:55,635
A MOVIE ABOUT CHAOTIC SURVIVAL
SET IN BOGOTA

202
00:08:55,701 --> 00:08:56,702
I'll die without that.

203
00:08:59,639 --> 00:09:01,374
<i>We have to make it there alive.</i>

204
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:05,678
Joong-ki, I heard you had
the best team dinner of your life

205
00:09:05,745 --> 00:09:08,381
-in Bogota.
-I see.

206
00:09:10,449 --> 00:09:13,719
I don't think any team dinner will
ever beat that one.

207
00:09:13,786 --> 00:09:16,556
-He looked out into the distance.
-What happened?

208
00:09:16,622 --> 00:09:18,691
-He went back to that day.
-Yes.

209
00:09:18,758 --> 00:09:20,426
-He just reminisced.
-He went back there.

210
00:09:20,493 --> 00:09:21,594
What was it like?

211
00:09:21,661 --> 00:09:26,265
<i>There were</i>
<i>about 100 Colombian staff members,</i>

212
00:09:26,332 --> 00:09:28,801
as well as around 70 Koreans.

213
00:09:28,868 --> 00:09:30,169
That's a huge crew.

214
00:09:30,236 --> 00:09:34,173
The team dinner was put together
while the crew's spirit was low.

215
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:36,175
I decided to host the event

216
00:09:36,242 --> 00:09:40,713
thinking I should make a fool of myself
for everyone to let loose and hang out.

217
00:09:40,780 --> 00:09:42,448
-To help them relax.
-Yes.

218
00:09:42,515 --> 00:09:43,950
-He's the life of the party.
-How thoughtful.

219
00:09:44,016 --> 00:09:47,954
-It's not easy to do.
-I also have hosted <i>Music Bank</i> before.

220
00:09:48,020 --> 00:09:49,221
-You were.
-Yes.

221
00:09:49,288 --> 00:09:51,190
-I did it for about two years.
-Yes.

222
00:09:51,257 --> 00:09:56,128
We rented out a Korean restaurant
and invited our entire production crew

223
00:09:56,195 --> 00:09:58,064
in an attempt to increase teamwork.

224
00:09:58,130 --> 00:10:00,299
So I decided to host it
just as I've done before.

225
00:10:00,366 --> 00:10:02,101
-I see.
-That was that.

226
00:10:02,168 --> 00:10:06,272
One of the Korean staff members
got their turn to sing a song.

227
00:10:06,339 --> 00:10:08,074
-It was just a song.
-Yes.

228
00:10:08,140 --> 00:10:10,076
Then, out of the blue…

229
00:10:10,142 --> 00:10:11,310
Someone must've been excited.

230
00:10:11,377 --> 00:10:13,913
…one of the Colombian staff members

231
00:10:13,980 --> 00:10:15,414
began to do the salsa dance.

232
00:10:15,481 --> 00:10:17,049
-I see.
-Salsa?

233
00:10:17,116 --> 00:10:19,218
They heard someone sing
and returned it by dancing salsa?

234
00:10:19,285 --> 00:10:21,887
I thought, "Okay, good."

235
00:10:21,954 --> 00:10:23,489
Yes, we can't lose.

236
00:10:23,556 --> 00:10:27,960
He had been getting salsa lessons
from one of the locals.

237
00:10:28,027 --> 00:10:29,228
Wait, there?

238
00:10:29,295 --> 00:10:32,632
I asked him to show us his moves,
and thankfully, he did.

239
00:10:32,698 --> 00:10:35,701
And the dance-off
went back and forth a few more times.

240
00:10:35,768 --> 00:10:38,638
How do you do the salsa dance?
I've never seen it before.

241
00:10:38,704 --> 00:10:41,307
-I shouldn't have said that.
-How does it go?

242
00:10:41,374 --> 00:10:45,978
It's already been 20 years
since Hee-jun made his debut.

243
00:10:46,045 --> 00:10:48,414
He has a dish he never eats
because of the memories

244
00:10:48,481 --> 00:10:50,383
from his anonymous days.

245
00:10:50,449 --> 00:10:53,986
He must've had tough memories
from that time.

246
00:10:54,053 --> 00:10:55,221
What is it?

247
00:10:55,287 --> 00:10:57,623
-It's ramyeon.
-Ramyeon.

248
00:10:57,690 --> 00:10:59,425
Did you eat a lot of ramyeon back then?

249
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:01,727
When times are tough,
that's the food you go for.

250
00:11:01,794 --> 00:11:05,097
I only ate ramyeon while I was in theater.

251
00:11:05,164 --> 00:11:08,234
This was when I lived
in a low-rent boarding called <i>gosiwon</i>.

252
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:13,339
The place always had rice
in the rice cooker, though.

253
00:11:13,406 --> 00:11:15,908
The smallest amount of money
I could spend on meals was this.

254
00:11:15,975 --> 00:11:19,512
I'd buy a big-sized Shin Ramyun
and eat only the noodles for breakfast.

255
00:11:19,578 --> 00:11:24,116
I'd keep the soup in the fridge,
come back at night, and mix rice in it.

256
00:11:24,183 --> 00:11:27,720
-I could eat for a day for just 800 won.
-Right.

257
00:11:27,787 --> 00:11:32,224
I shared this at my admission interview
for Korea National University of Arts,

258
00:11:32,291 --> 00:11:35,628
and the professor asked,
"What would you do if not acting?"

259
00:11:36,295 --> 00:11:39,165
I answered, "Whatever that can help me
stop eating ramyeon."

260
00:11:39,231 --> 00:11:41,067
-He must've been that sick of it.
-It's heartbreaking.

261
00:11:41,133 --> 00:11:43,969
I think that was why I got in. Anyway.

262
00:11:44,036 --> 00:11:47,973
Back then,
ramyeon was a precious commodity,

263
00:11:48,641 --> 00:11:53,646
but even as I think back on it now,
it was still hard to eat.

264
00:11:53,713 --> 00:11:56,816
It wasn't like
you had a bag of ramyeon every meal.

265
00:11:56,882 --> 00:11:58,684
-You had one ramyeon…
-He split it up.

266
00:11:58,751 --> 00:12:01,387
…then split it up into noodles and soup.

267
00:12:01,454 --> 00:12:04,623
I have a question.
What if you're offered a ramyeon ad?

268
00:12:04,690 --> 00:12:06,092
I'll take it.

269
00:12:06,158 --> 00:12:09,028
I CAN'T HOLD BACK FROM DOING THAT

270
00:12:09,095 --> 00:12:10,696
-You have to eat it deliciously.
-Yes.

271
00:12:10,763 --> 00:12:12,298
You have to make it look good.

272
00:12:12,364 --> 00:12:14,667
-Ramyeon is a necessity for Koreans.
-Right?

273
00:12:14,734 --> 00:12:15,968
Yes, that's right.

274
00:12:16,035 --> 00:12:18,237
-You can eat it anytime, anywhere.
-Yes.

275
00:12:18,304 --> 00:12:20,339
-You can even…
-Come on.

276
00:12:20,406 --> 00:12:22,274
Joong-ki just pointed his finger at you.

277
00:12:23,342 --> 00:12:26,278
-Well, that's a different issue.
-Yes.

278
00:12:26,345 --> 00:12:29,048
I also heard you exchange empty bottles

279
00:12:29,115 --> 00:12:31,117
for jjajang ramyeon.

280
00:12:31,183 --> 00:12:34,086
-I suddenly remembered this today.
-I see.

281
00:12:34,153 --> 00:12:36,956
This was while I was in theater arts,
while I still lived in a <i>gosiwon</i>.

282
00:12:37,022 --> 00:12:39,191
An older friend in the industry
lived in a rooftop unit,

283
00:12:39,258 --> 00:12:41,227
and he told me to move in with him

284
00:12:41,293 --> 00:12:43,162
so I could sleep more at ease.

285
00:12:43,229 --> 00:12:47,967
He lived in a studio unit where
his fridge sat right next to his door.

286
00:12:48,033 --> 00:12:50,202
So I lived for another year
in front of that fridge.

287
00:12:50,269 --> 00:12:52,571
-In front of that fridge?
-You must've heard its noise.

288
00:12:52,638 --> 00:12:55,374
Even now, when I hear the fridge sound,

289
00:12:55,441 --> 00:12:58,577
it feels like something you'll play
to help babies sleep.

290
00:12:58,644 --> 00:13:00,279
It feels like white noise.

291
00:13:00,346 --> 00:13:02,782
-It's relaxing. I did that for a year.
-You feel relaxed?

292
00:13:02,848 --> 00:13:04,517
You have a connection with fridges.

293
00:13:05,317 --> 00:13:08,621
-He basically does.
-It's not for its functions, though.

294
00:13:08,687 --> 00:13:11,624
Around 1:00 to 2:00 a.m.,

295
00:13:11,690 --> 00:13:15,361
drunken fellow theater actors
would come over while I was asleep.

296
00:13:15,427 --> 00:13:16,929
To that rooftop unit.

297
00:13:16,996 --> 00:13:19,198
They all had a drink
in front of that fridge,

298
00:13:19,265 --> 00:13:22,835
so the place was
always filled with empty bottles.

299
00:13:22,902 --> 00:13:26,572
I'd sell those bottles
for ramyeon and live off that.

300
00:13:26,639 --> 00:13:29,175
If you get an ad for jjajang ramyeon,
will you accept or not?

301
00:13:30,276 --> 00:13:32,511
I still can't forget
the Chapagetti I had then.

302
00:13:34,346 --> 00:13:36,382
-Delicious.
-My gosh.

303
00:13:36,448 --> 00:13:39,485
-This kind of story will work nicely.
-Yes.

304
00:13:39,552 --> 00:13:42,221
He might get a fridge ad
and sleep in front of it.

305
00:13:42,288 --> 00:13:44,056
I'D LOVE FOR IT TO HAPPEN

306
00:13:44,123 --> 00:13:45,658
This is not noise.

307
00:13:46,926 --> 00:13:49,728
-The fridge noise is a lullaby.
-Yes. It's a lullaby.

308
00:13:49,795 --> 00:13:51,397
-It's a lullaby.
-Of course.

309
00:13:51,463 --> 00:13:54,433
It must've been tough,
but I'm glad he can tell us with a smile.

310
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:56,202
-Right.
-Yes.

311
00:13:56,769 --> 00:13:59,572
Before we present Hee-jun's fridge,

312
00:13:59,638 --> 00:14:02,641
let us find out his order

313
00:14:02,708 --> 00:14:04,910
and decide on the contenders.

314
00:14:04,977 --> 00:14:07,813
Let us check his order. Show us!

315
00:14:08,314 --> 00:14:09,348
COOK-OFF WITH LEE HEE-JUN'S FRIDGE

316
00:14:09,415 --> 00:14:12,718
His first order is,
"I want to taste the state of art."

317
00:14:12,785 --> 00:14:15,855
While I watched <i>Culinary Class Wars,</i>

318
00:14:15,921 --> 00:14:17,790
I thought it was like art.

319
00:14:17,857 --> 00:14:19,592
I'm in theater arts,

320
00:14:19,658 --> 00:14:21,360
and I'd practice for two to three months.

321
00:14:21,894 --> 00:14:24,930
And every day, the play I put on is
only for that audience's eyes.

322
00:14:24,997 --> 00:14:26,632
-Yes.
-It disappears after that.

323
00:14:26,699 --> 00:14:28,567
So when I watched the cooking show,

324
00:14:28,634 --> 00:14:32,404
I saw how you layered the food,
smoke them, and do all kinds of things,

325
00:14:32,471 --> 00:14:35,040
but it disappears
the moment one person eats it.

326
00:14:35,107 --> 00:14:38,010
But I never experienced
different layers in a dish.

327
00:14:38,077 --> 00:14:41,280
I wanted to try something like that too.

328
00:14:41,347 --> 00:14:44,717
-The next one is the must-eat restaurants.
-The must-eat restaurants.

329
00:14:44,783 --> 00:14:49,054
I'm the type who prioritizes time
and doesn't like to waste it,

330
00:14:49,121 --> 00:14:51,223
so I've never lined up
to eat at a popular restaurant.

331
00:14:51,290 --> 00:14:53,592
-Some are like you.
-They are.

332
00:14:53,659 --> 00:14:58,230
But I do get curious
about why people line up like that.

333
00:14:58,831 --> 00:15:01,400
-And you want to taste that here.
-Yes.

334
00:15:01,467 --> 00:15:03,602
Simply put,
you want to eat it without the line.

335
00:15:03,669 --> 00:15:06,205
Yes, that's exactly it.

336
00:15:06,272 --> 00:15:09,108
-That's it. You don't want to line up.
-Yes.

337
00:15:09,174 --> 00:15:12,044
Don't you think they're similar?

338
00:15:12,111 --> 00:15:14,680
People will only line up
to taste the state of art.

339
00:15:14,747 --> 00:15:18,684
And now, if you feel confident enough,
please raise your hand.

340
00:15:18,751 --> 00:15:20,386
I'll do it.

341
00:15:21,820 --> 00:15:22,855
YAY

342
00:15:22,922 --> 00:15:27,493
-It's Chef Hyun-suk, Hee-jun's favorite.
-Thank you.

343
00:15:27,559 --> 00:15:30,095
It broke my heart that
he wanted a job that wouldn't force him

344
00:15:30,162 --> 00:15:31,497
to eat ramyeon all the time.

345
00:15:31,563 --> 00:15:33,599
There are
so many delicious things in life,

346
00:15:33,666 --> 00:15:35,901
and you can feel happiness
through those flavors.

347
00:15:35,968 --> 00:15:39,772
So I'd like to make you a dish
that's state of art.

348
00:15:39,838 --> 00:15:42,374
-My gosh.
-State of art.

349
00:15:42,441 --> 00:15:45,778
I want to show him

350
00:15:45,844 --> 00:15:48,480
the reason why chefs exist in the world.

351
00:15:48,547 --> 00:15:51,450
I both want to make this
and make him line up at my restaurant.

352
00:15:51,517 --> 00:15:53,319
Two birds with one stone.

353
00:15:53,385 --> 00:15:55,688
THE MOST CLEVER CHEF HERE HAS TWO GOALS

354
00:15:55,754 --> 00:15:57,790
Chef Hyun-suk takes a spot.

355
00:15:57,856 --> 00:16:00,092
Sam, shouldn't you fight him?

356
00:16:00,159 --> 00:16:01,794
A state-of-the-art flavor.

357
00:16:01,860 --> 00:16:05,230
-Shouldn't Chef Yeon-bok go?
-What about Chef Ho-young?

358
00:16:05,931 --> 00:16:07,366
-I'll go.
-Wait.

359
00:16:07,433 --> 00:16:09,401
Why would you join this artistic battle?

360
00:16:09,468 --> 00:16:11,437
Because it's art!

361
00:16:11,503 --> 00:16:13,539
-Why wouldn't I go?
-Yes.

362
00:16:13,605 --> 00:16:15,741
Scared?

363
00:16:16,308 --> 00:16:17,710
Annoyed.

364
00:16:18,510 --> 00:16:20,379
-I'm annoyed.
-Gosh.

365
00:16:20,446 --> 00:16:24,116
I'm the only art major among these chefs.

366
00:16:24,183 --> 00:16:27,119
-Yes, majoring in cartoons.
-Yes, you're an artist.

367
00:16:27,186 --> 00:16:29,221
It'll be something you never had before.

368
00:16:29,288 --> 00:16:31,056
You'll find yourself saying,

369
00:16:31,123 --> 00:16:32,858
"How does food taste like this?"

370
00:16:32,925 --> 00:16:38,230
I also like to add different flavors
and textures into a dish.

371
00:16:38,998 --> 00:16:40,899
The dishes Poong tend to make

372
00:16:40,966 --> 00:16:42,668
wasn't really my type.

373
00:16:44,536 --> 00:16:47,039
-Will you refuse him for the first time?
-No.

374
00:16:47,106 --> 00:16:50,275
I'll destroy that prejudice
artistically today.

375
00:16:50,342 --> 00:16:51,577
All right.

376
00:16:52,177 --> 00:16:54,880
Then who'll take the must-eat restaurants?

377
00:16:54,947 --> 00:16:56,348
I'll do it.

378
00:16:56,415 --> 00:16:59,818
Chef Yeon-bok!
Chef Yeon-bok joins the round.

379
00:16:59,885 --> 00:17:01,020
My gosh.

380
00:17:01,086 --> 00:17:02,254
Do you have a reason?

381
00:17:02,321 --> 00:17:05,958
I've always seen a line at my restaurant
since when I was much younger.

382
00:17:06,025 --> 00:17:06,859
Yes, it's been a while.

383
00:17:06,925 --> 00:17:10,929
One of the returning chefs
have taken a seat first. The second…

384
00:17:10,996 --> 00:17:11,930
I'll do it.

385
00:17:11,997 --> 00:17:14,867
-It's Park Eun-yeong!
-The Chinese cuisine battle.

386
00:17:14,933 --> 00:17:16,969
Yes, Chinese versus Chinese.

387
00:17:17,036 --> 00:17:17,903
Are you sure?

388
00:17:17,970 --> 00:17:20,806
My restaurant in Hong Kong
always have customers lined up,

389
00:17:20,873 --> 00:17:23,008
so I'm also perfect for the order.

390
00:17:23,075 --> 00:17:27,212
What's also important is that
I wanted to fight the legendary chef.

391
00:17:27,279 --> 00:17:30,883
-So the old Chinese chef must disappear?
-Old Chinese chef?

392
00:17:30,949 --> 00:17:31,917
I didn't say old.

393
00:17:31,984 --> 00:17:35,320
-Goodbye, old Chinese chef.
-I didn't mean that he was old.

394
00:17:35,387 --> 00:17:36,822
The young Chinese chef is here.

395
00:17:36,889 --> 00:17:39,224
This may make them
too uncomfortable to meet ever again.

396
00:17:39,291 --> 00:17:40,559
That sounds like trouble.

397
00:17:40,626 --> 00:17:44,196
In that case, let us present
the ingredients in the fridge.

398
00:17:44,263 --> 00:17:46,598
Please take a good look.

399
00:17:46,665 --> 00:17:49,034
-We'll comb through everything.
-Yes.

400
00:17:49,101 --> 00:17:53,238
-It must be his son's drawing.
-Were these all drawn by your son?

401
00:17:53,305 --> 00:17:55,040
-How heartwarming.
-I see.

402
00:17:55,107 --> 00:17:56,708
-I have one son.
-You have one son, right?

403
00:17:56,775 --> 00:17:59,244
-And he loves to draw with me.
-I see.

404
00:17:59,311 --> 00:18:02,047
-We actually made huge drawings together.
-I see.

405
00:18:02,114 --> 00:18:05,651
-He also loves <i>Miniforce</i>, so he drew them.
-<i>Miniforce</i>.

406
00:18:05,717 --> 00:18:09,054
-Did your son draw that?
-I drew it with my son.

407
00:18:09,121 --> 00:18:12,491
Something about that drawing
with the three of us is kind of funny.

408
00:18:12,558 --> 00:18:15,194
My wife put it up there after he drew it,
but I wasn't in it.

409
00:18:15,260 --> 00:18:17,262
-I see.
-Why not?

410
00:18:17,329 --> 00:18:21,200
I wasn't in there,
so I mimicked his drawing and put me in.

411
00:18:21,834 --> 00:18:23,702
-Did you mimic his drawing?
-Yes.

412
00:18:23,769 --> 00:18:26,772
The daddy with the mustache
wasn't in it before.

413
00:18:26,839 --> 00:18:29,408
It does look like
it was drawn by an adult.

414
00:18:29,475 --> 00:18:32,811
-Those are our marriage vows.
-Your marriage vows.

415
00:18:32,878 --> 00:18:34,680
-How romantic.
-It's where you can see it.

416
00:18:34,746 --> 00:18:35,581
Our vows.

417
00:18:35,647 --> 00:18:37,549
Do you have a pet name for each other?

418
00:18:37,616 --> 00:18:41,687
-We call each other honey pie.
-"Honey pie."

419
00:18:41,753 --> 00:18:43,422
-Do you have pet names?
-Yes.

420
00:18:43,489 --> 00:18:45,257
-My wife chose it.
-Okay.

421
00:18:45,324 --> 00:18:46,625
We call each other <i>yeobo</i>.

422
00:18:46,692 --> 00:18:50,229
-<i>Yeobo</i>.
-She heard the word honey in Korean,

423
00:18:50,295 --> 00:18:53,332
and loved how the word <i>yeobo</i> sounded,

424
00:18:53,398 --> 00:18:54,900
so she wanted to do that.

425
00:18:54,967 --> 00:18:56,935
<i>Yeobo </i>and honey pie.

426
00:18:57,002 --> 00:18:58,704
That word honey has a good ring.

427
00:18:58,770 --> 00:19:02,741
We present Lee Hee-jun's fridge!

428
00:19:03,542 --> 00:19:07,279
My gosh. Take a good look, chefs.

429
00:19:07,346 --> 00:19:11,183
-My gosh. Take a good look, chefs.
-There are lots of food.

430
00:19:11,250 --> 00:19:13,519
It's filled with food,

431
00:19:13,585 --> 00:19:15,454
much more than last time.

432
00:19:15,521 --> 00:19:17,823
This one caught my eyes first.

433
00:19:17,890 --> 00:19:19,558
Is this mala sauce?

434
00:19:19,625 --> 00:19:21,994
-Mala sauce?
-Mala sauce?

435
00:19:22,060 --> 00:19:23,262
Look, mala sauce.

436
00:19:23,328 --> 00:19:25,764
-It's about a third empty.
-Yes.

437
00:19:25,831 --> 00:19:28,267
This is Lao Gan Ma,
the numbing Chinese chili oil sauce.

438
00:19:28,333 --> 00:19:29,801
Do you like Chinese food?

439
00:19:29,868 --> 00:19:31,703
I don't. My wife does.

440
00:19:31,770 --> 00:19:33,705
DISHEARTENED CHINESE CHEFS

441
00:19:33,772 --> 00:19:36,508
I don't like overly spicy and salty food.

442
00:19:36,575 --> 00:19:39,411
-You must like bland food.
-I like clean and healthy tastes.

443
00:19:39,478 --> 00:19:41,313
You're done.

444
00:19:41,380 --> 00:19:42,915
Kind of like temple food.

445
00:19:42,981 --> 00:19:44,983
-Temple food?
-Temple food?

446
00:19:45,050 --> 00:19:46,351
So you don't like noodles?

447
00:19:46,418 --> 00:19:47,452
I don't like noodles.

448
00:19:47,519 --> 00:19:49,988
Do you not eat food made with flour?

449
00:19:50,055 --> 00:19:51,790
I have trouble digesting flour.

450
00:19:51,857 --> 00:19:53,125
-Indigestion.
-I see.

451
00:19:53,192 --> 00:19:55,160
Maybe I'm just particular,

452
00:19:55,227 --> 00:19:58,530
but I can't handle food
that looks displeasing.

453
00:19:58,597 --> 00:20:02,334
I can never eat pork rind or chicken feet.

454
00:20:02,401 --> 00:20:06,138
My wife loves chicken feet,
but she won't eat it around me.

455
00:20:07,139 --> 00:20:10,442
What was your favorite dish
among what your wife cooked for you?

456
00:20:10,509 --> 00:20:14,513
-I always love seaweed soup, miyeok-guk.
-Miyeok-guk.

457
00:20:14,580 --> 00:20:18,483
When you make it with seaweed form Gijang,
the soup turns murky white.

458
00:20:18,550 --> 00:20:19,685
It's absolutely delicious.

459
00:20:20,252 --> 00:20:22,087
I always mix rice
into seaweed soup in the morning.

460
00:20:22,154 --> 00:20:24,690
-So every day must be your birthday.
-Yes, pretty much.

461
00:20:24,756 --> 00:20:27,059
-His favorite is miyeok-guk.
-Made by his wife.

462
00:20:27,125 --> 00:20:30,329
My wife mostly cooks her food
within 15 minutes.

463
00:20:30,395 --> 00:20:31,863
SERIOUSLY AMAZED

464
00:20:31,930 --> 00:20:33,298
She's pretty talented.

465
00:20:33,365 --> 00:20:35,033
She should be here soon.

466
00:20:35,100 --> 00:20:36,702
My gosh.

467
00:20:36,768 --> 00:20:39,071
His wife is a seriously good cook.

468
00:20:39,137 --> 00:20:40,706
-Really?
-I see.

469
00:20:40,772 --> 00:20:41,840
When you go to his place,

470
00:20:41,907 --> 00:20:44,343
she keeps on serving
one dish after another.

471
00:20:45,277 --> 00:20:47,279
Do you hold many parties at home?

472
00:20:47,346 --> 00:20:50,148
I've had over 700 to 800 guests so far.

473
00:20:50,215 --> 00:20:52,718
-Wait, 700 to 800?
-Since I debuted 20 years ago.

474
00:20:52,784 --> 00:20:56,388
Was there any memorable party food
your wife made?

475
00:20:56,455 --> 00:20:58,090
It depends on the guest.

476
00:20:58,156 --> 00:21:01,493
Everything is delicious, but at times,
she'd cook spicy braised chicken,

477
00:21:01,560 --> 00:21:04,529
but on the day Son Suk-ku came,
she suddenly made a never-before-seen dish

478
00:21:04,596 --> 00:21:06,131
like salmon papillote.

479
00:21:06,198 --> 00:21:07,199
SHE MADE SALMON PAPILLOTE!

480
00:21:07,833 --> 00:21:09,201
She does that?

481
00:21:09,268 --> 00:21:11,803
The menu changes.

482
00:21:11,870 --> 00:21:13,739
If we visit, she'll order us some food.

483
00:21:15,207 --> 00:21:17,309
-Yes.
-If we go, she'll get delivery food.

484
00:21:17,376 --> 00:21:19,945
-She could go, "I'm sorry, I was busy."
-That can happen.

485
00:21:20,012 --> 00:21:21,947
-Yes.
-That pickled green onion is great.

486
00:21:22,014 --> 00:21:24,016
-Pickled green onion?
-Pickled green onion?

487
00:21:24,082 --> 00:21:26,051
We have pickled garlic cloves
and green onion.

488
00:21:26,118 --> 00:21:26,952
She's good at making pickles.

489
00:21:27,019 --> 00:21:29,888
-Is this something to your taste?
-It's so good.

490
00:21:29,955 --> 00:21:31,290
-Do you eat it often?
-Yes.

491
00:21:31,356 --> 00:21:35,060
This is something that he likes.

492
00:21:35,127 --> 00:21:36,862
-It looks good.
-Okay.

493
00:21:36,928 --> 00:21:40,032
-I've never seen pickled green onion.
-It's good.

494
00:21:40,098 --> 00:21:42,567
-Right? With green onion?
-It's good. It's really good.

495
00:21:42,634 --> 00:21:44,870
-It smells good.
-Okay.

496
00:21:45,637 --> 00:21:49,508
THE CHEFS ARE ALL BUSY
GETTING A TASTE, AND…

497
00:21:49,574 --> 00:21:51,376
-I'm sorry, but let Joong-ki have a taste.
-Yes, Joong-ki.

498
00:21:51,443 --> 00:21:54,313
He said it smelled great,
but you passed him by.

499
00:21:54,379 --> 00:21:56,815
I wanted the chefs to have a taste.

500
00:21:56,882 --> 00:21:58,317
Thank you.

501
00:21:58,383 --> 00:21:59,918
He meant that he wanted one.

502
00:22:00,786 --> 00:22:02,154
Is it okay?

503
00:22:02,220 --> 00:22:04,089
-It's so good?
-Is it?

504
00:22:04,156 --> 00:22:06,058
I've never had pickled green onion before.

505
00:22:06,124 --> 00:22:10,095
-Kimchi.
-This kimchi jar has stickers on it.

506
00:22:10,162 --> 00:22:13,465
My six-year-old son
made that at kindergarten.

507
00:22:13,532 --> 00:22:16,034
-Your son made that?
-Whoa, really?

508
00:22:16,101 --> 00:22:17,836
He's much better than me.

509
00:22:17,903 --> 00:22:20,138
-You had quite a lot.
-Yes.

510
00:22:20,205 --> 00:22:22,007
He loved to see me eat it,

511
00:22:22,074 --> 00:22:25,344
-so he kept asking me to eat it.
-You must've said it was good.

512
00:22:25,410 --> 00:22:26,345
I'm so jealous.

513
00:22:26,411 --> 00:22:28,180
-Your child will do this soon too.
-Very soon.

514
00:22:28,246 --> 00:22:30,449
Your son will make pasta.

515
00:22:30,515 --> 00:22:33,452
There are vegetables here.

516
00:22:33,518 --> 00:22:36,955
Kale, cabbage, napa cabbage, and carrot.

517
00:22:37,022 --> 00:22:39,191
How do you usually eat your veggies?

518
00:22:39,257 --> 00:22:41,593
I eat it raw by dipping it in truffle oil.

519
00:22:41,660 --> 00:22:44,296
How does that taste?
It must be odd without any flavor.

520
00:22:44,363 --> 00:22:45,964
I have a question.

521
00:22:46,031 --> 00:22:48,400
Do you dip vegetables in truffle oil

522
00:22:48,467 --> 00:22:51,002
out of enjoyment
or because of health benefits?

523
00:22:51,069 --> 00:22:52,604
Actually,

524
00:22:52,671 --> 00:22:55,507
I don't think
I cared much about flavors to this day.

525
00:22:56,108 --> 00:22:59,077
I almost choked up
when Chef Hyun-suk just said

526
00:22:59,144 --> 00:23:01,680
that there are
many delicious dishes in this world.

527
00:23:01,747 --> 00:23:03,281
All I ever cared about was

528
00:23:03,348 --> 00:23:05,784
-eating my food quickly
-You were busy.

529
00:23:05,851 --> 00:23:07,152
to read scripts and practice.

530
00:23:07,219 --> 00:23:09,254
That's why you can't understand

531
00:23:09,321 --> 00:23:11,289
-people who line up at restaurants.
-Right.

532
00:23:11,356 --> 00:23:14,526
-I think this is for weight loss.
-Yes.

533
00:23:14,593 --> 00:23:18,230
I'm sure that's the case for all actors.
I must eat a certain way to lose weight.

534
00:23:18,296 --> 00:23:21,066
That's for weight gain. Peanut butter.

535
00:23:21,133 --> 00:23:22,634
-It's for weight gain.
-Wait.

536
00:23:22,701 --> 00:23:24,169
For <i>The Man Standing Next</i>

537
00:23:24,236 --> 00:23:26,371
<i>I started at 75 kg</i>
<i>and gained 25 kg to reach 100 kg.</i>

538
00:23:26,438 --> 00:23:27,506
<i>Gosh, 25 kg?</i>

539
00:23:27,572 --> 00:23:29,141
I'd spread peanut butter over bread.

540
00:23:29,207 --> 00:23:31,443
-He ate it with bread.
-I had to eat a lot.

541
00:23:31,510 --> 00:23:33,512
I like the one with jelly.

542
00:23:33,578 --> 00:23:35,547
It's way too dry.

543
00:23:35,614 --> 00:23:37,616
Hey, why do you care about what I like?

544
00:23:38,250 --> 00:23:39,251
It's what I like!

545
00:23:39,317 --> 00:23:41,353
I like that product.

546
00:23:41,420 --> 00:23:44,589
Each to one's own, but I'm saying
that one is dry, but this one is soft.

547
00:23:44,656 --> 00:23:46,191
The chef is fighting the host.

548
00:23:46,258 --> 00:23:49,294
What did I do? I mix it with the jelly.

549
00:23:49,361 --> 00:23:52,297
-The jelly and the peanut butter.
-That's enough. Stop it.

550
00:23:52,364 --> 00:23:55,500
I mean, he didn't even win that show.

551
00:23:55,567 --> 00:23:56,568
Come on.

552
00:23:57,068 --> 00:23:58,570
You shouldn't fight the chef.

553
00:23:58,637 --> 00:24:00,105
We can say that when we're alone.

554
00:24:00,172 --> 00:24:01,339
He was in eighth place.

555
00:24:01,406 --> 00:24:02,541
-Eighth?
-Yes, I asked him.

556
00:24:02,607 --> 00:24:04,075
No one counts that as a rank.

557
00:24:04,142 --> 00:24:05,977
Come on. Stop it.

558
00:24:06,044 --> 00:24:08,180
The first place is here,
so don't say that.

559
00:24:08,246 --> 00:24:10,015
He won't even let me say what I like.

560
00:24:10,081 --> 00:24:12,751
Okay. We're moving on to the freezer.

561
00:24:12,818 --> 00:24:14,085
-Gosh.
-There are lots of meat.

562
00:24:14,152 --> 00:24:16,955
-Yes, I see thin pork belly.
-Thin pork belly.

563
00:24:17,022 --> 00:24:18,457
Do you prefer seafood to red meat?

564
00:24:18,523 --> 00:24:20,425
-Yes, I like seafood better.
-He prefers seafood.

565
00:24:20,492 --> 00:24:24,129
-I found them here. Seafood.
-There they are.

566
00:24:24,196 --> 00:24:26,331
-Yes, I found some octopus.
-It looks great.

567
00:24:26,398 --> 00:24:28,533
Don't you find this gross to look at?

568
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:29,434
It looks adorable.

569
00:24:30,869 --> 00:24:33,805
His evaluation differs every time.

570
00:24:34,539 --> 00:24:36,341
Look at all the fish.

571
00:24:36,408 --> 00:24:37,476
Atka mackerel.

572
00:24:37,542 --> 00:24:38,777
-Yes.
-Tilefish.

573
00:24:38,844 --> 00:24:39,945
Tonguefish.

574
00:24:40,011 --> 00:24:41,213
-Tonguefish is good.
-Really.

575
00:24:41,279 --> 00:24:45,150
-I have no idea.
-We looked through his fridge.

576
00:24:45,217 --> 00:24:48,987
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

577
00:24:49,054 --> 00:24:51,156
LET THE 15-MINUTE COOK-OFF BEGIN

578
00:24:51,223 --> 00:24:52,491
This seems hard.

579
00:24:53,358 --> 00:24:54,759
KIM POONG VS CHOI HYUN-SUK

580
00:24:54,826 --> 00:24:57,996
Let us begin the cook-off
with ingredients from Hee-jun's fridge.

581
00:24:58,630 --> 00:25:02,167
These two are the true sworn enemies
of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

582
00:25:02,234 --> 00:25:05,337
Chef Choi Hyun-suk
versus webtoon artist Kim Poong.

583
00:25:05,403 --> 00:25:08,173
We can't call them a rival
if you consider their record.

584
00:25:08,240 --> 00:25:10,575
Seven rounds, six wins, and one defeat.

585
00:25:11,209 --> 00:25:14,079
Choi Hyun-suk has an overwhelming lead.

586
00:25:14,145 --> 00:25:16,948
You lost once
when Mr. Park Geun-hyung was here.

587
00:25:17,015 --> 00:25:19,150
This jeongol is missing tofu.

588
00:25:19,217 --> 00:25:21,086
It's such a shame.

589
00:25:21,152 --> 00:25:23,088
-It's such a shame.
-It's such a shame.

590
00:25:23,154 --> 00:25:24,756
You lost once at that time.

591
00:25:24,823 --> 00:25:26,858
Are you missing anything?
Is everything ready?

592
00:25:26,925 --> 00:25:28,126
-Yes.
-I see.

593
00:25:28,627 --> 00:25:31,630
I have something to say.
He said he wasn't missing anything,

594
00:25:31,696 --> 00:25:34,165
but he must've forgotten his knife.
He borrowed mine.

595
00:25:34,232 --> 00:25:36,167
-Your knife?
-You borrowed his knife?

596
00:25:36,234 --> 00:25:37,469
You forgot your knife?

597
00:25:37,536 --> 00:25:39,971
That's like a soldier
going to war without a gun.

598
00:25:40,038 --> 00:25:42,073
-He's borrowing someone else's knife?
-Yes.

599
00:25:42,140 --> 00:25:44,075
Well, the important thing is this.
Chef Hyun-suk is here

600
00:25:44,142 --> 00:25:47,178
-as a new chef who was on that show.
-Yes.

601
00:25:47,245 --> 00:25:50,782
Does this mean
he's allowed to use the perks?

602
00:25:50,849 --> 00:25:52,817
That's very important right now.

603
00:25:52,884 --> 00:25:54,519
Just an FYI, last time, you said…

604
00:25:54,586 --> 00:25:58,356
The 15-minute rule is
the foundation of <i>Chef & My Fridge.</i>

605
00:25:58,423 --> 00:26:02,360
…using this perk could
destroy the sanctity of this show.

606
00:26:02,427 --> 00:26:04,563
He wouldn't do that against Poong.

607
00:26:04,629 --> 00:26:06,698
If he does, it'll make him seem too dirty.

608
00:26:06,765 --> 00:26:09,000
-But the rule still exists.
-It does.

609
00:26:09,067 --> 00:26:10,702
-We should ask him.
-We should.

610
00:26:10,769 --> 00:26:12,737
He's up against Artist Kim Poong.

611
00:26:12,804 --> 00:26:13,805
Will he use it?

612
00:26:13,872 --> 00:26:17,075
Will one of Korea's best chefs,
Chef Choi Hyun-suk…

613
00:26:17,142 --> 00:26:18,343
I want to find out.

614
00:26:18,410 --> 00:26:20,178
…give a penalty to his opponent?

615
00:26:20,245 --> 00:26:23,048
So? Would you like to shake
the very foundation of the show?

616
00:26:23,114 --> 00:26:25,116
I'm a chef who always plays by the rules.

617
00:26:25,183 --> 00:26:27,452
If we set a rule, we must observe it.

618
00:26:27,519 --> 00:26:28,687
Sheesh.

619
00:26:28,753 --> 00:26:30,288
He doesn't care about the foundation.

620
00:26:30,355 --> 00:26:32,223
-Good grief.
-Right.

621
00:26:32,290 --> 00:26:34,859
So? Will you start early or stop him?

622
00:26:34,926 --> 00:26:36,161
I'll watch the situation.

623
00:26:36,895 --> 00:26:38,063
And wait.

624
00:26:38,997 --> 00:26:42,634
This means he'll use
the one-minute stopper.

625
00:26:43,468 --> 00:26:44,536
KIM POONG'S INGREDIENTS

626
00:26:44,603 --> 00:26:46,705
SEAFOOD BROTH, TOFU, SEAWEED,
SHRIMP, UNI, OYSTER SAUCE

627
00:26:46,771 --> 00:26:47,806
HYUN-SUK'S INGREDIENTS:

628
00:26:47,872 --> 00:26:48,873
PORK, ATKA MACKEREL
AND TONGUEFISH,

629
00:26:48,940 --> 00:26:50,642
PASSION FRUIT PRESERVES, SHRIMP,
LIME JUICE, TRUFFLE OIL, RED PEPPER

630
00:26:50,709 --> 00:26:51,943
What's your dish called?

631
00:26:52,010 --> 00:26:55,981
The dish I prepared is called
"I Have Got Tonguefish."

632
00:26:56,047 --> 00:26:58,783
-I Have Got Tonguefish.
-Tonguefish.

633
00:26:58,850 --> 00:27:01,620
Did you get the idea from the drama
<i>My Husband Got a Family</i>?

634
00:27:01,686 --> 00:27:02,988
-Yes.
-I see.

635
00:27:03,054 --> 00:27:04,956
I slowly became known
thanks to that drama.

636
00:27:05,023 --> 00:27:06,558
That's your biggest work yet.

637
00:27:06,625 --> 00:27:08,493
Hey, nice name.

638
00:27:08,560 --> 00:27:10,862
Are you trying to say
you watched a lot of his dramas?

639
00:27:10,929 --> 00:27:13,498
I wanted to ask Hee-jun to do one thing.

640
00:27:13,565 --> 00:27:17,002
Please leave out everything else
when you evaluate.

641
00:27:17,068 --> 00:27:19,704
Just judge us based on these dishes.

642
00:27:19,771 --> 00:27:23,274
-But it's called I Have Got Tonguefish.
-I Have Got Tonguefish.

643
00:27:23,341 --> 00:27:25,076
GOOD GRIEF

644
00:27:25,143 --> 00:27:26,411
How is this dish made?

645
00:27:26,478 --> 00:27:28,913
He said he wanted to taste
different layers of flavor.

646
00:27:28,980 --> 00:27:32,651
I want to make a dish
with layers of texture and flavor

647
00:27:32,717 --> 00:27:35,253
with an artistic touch.

648
00:27:35,320 --> 00:27:36,454
LOOK FORWARD TO IT

649
00:27:36,521 --> 00:27:37,989
Actually,

650
00:27:38,056 --> 00:27:40,158
he's using something not too delicious,

651
00:27:40,225 --> 00:27:43,061
something I bought
and only eat to lose weight.

652
00:27:43,128 --> 00:27:47,365
-My wife also tried to cook with that.
-But it wasn't good?

653
00:27:47,432 --> 00:27:48,433
But it wasn't good.

654
00:27:48,500 --> 00:27:51,202
HEE-JUN DIDN'T LIKE IT

655
00:27:51,269 --> 00:27:54,305
His wife is a rather good cook,
so if she failed

656
00:27:54,372 --> 00:27:56,074
He better make this real good.

657
00:27:56,141 --> 00:27:58,109
The dish I'll make is called

658
00:27:58,176 --> 00:28:00,245
Poong's Masterpiece.

659
00:28:00,311 --> 00:28:02,047
-Poong's Masterpiece.
-Poong's Masterpiece.

660
00:28:02,113 --> 00:28:03,448
GREAT NAME

661
00:28:03,515 --> 00:28:04,949
-That's a good name.
-It sounds like a TV show.

662
00:28:05,016 --> 00:28:06,451
-Yes.
-What's it like?

663
00:28:07,152 --> 00:28:08,620
"Fine dining."

664
00:28:08,687 --> 00:28:10,588
KIM POONG WILL DO THAT?
CAN'T BELIEVE THEIR EARS

665
00:28:10,655 --> 00:28:12,891
-"Fine dining."
-What?

666
00:28:13,558 --> 00:28:15,460
What does it mean, Chef Hyun-suk?

667
00:28:15,527 --> 00:28:17,095
Fine dining. Well.

668
00:28:17,162 --> 00:28:19,097
Good dining.

669
00:28:20,165 --> 00:28:22,901
You're in the fine dining business,
but you don't know what it means?

670
00:28:22,967 --> 00:28:24,669
I'm fine.

671
00:28:24,736 --> 00:28:27,338
Thank you, and you? All right, well.

672
00:28:27,405 --> 00:28:29,374
I always have
a lot of respect for the chefs.

673
00:28:29,441 --> 00:28:31,242
So when their dishes look great,

674
00:28:31,309 --> 00:28:33,278
I want to steal it from them.

675
00:28:33,344 --> 00:28:34,446
FLINCHES

676
00:28:34,512 --> 00:28:36,948
I want to steal
Chef Hyun-suk's flounder seaweed soup,

677
00:28:37,015 --> 00:28:40,552
the dish he made and blended
to make a different texture,

678
00:28:40,618 --> 00:28:43,288
and reinterpret it in my own style.

679
00:28:43,354 --> 00:28:44,989
-It must taste refreshing.
-On top of that,

680
00:28:45,056 --> 00:28:48,526
I also want to steal Chef Edward,
Chef Kyun's dish.

681
00:28:48,593 --> 00:28:50,795
-Do you remember his tteokbokki?
-Yes.

682
00:28:50,862 --> 00:28:52,931
I want to reinterpret that in my style

683
00:28:52,997 --> 00:28:57,469
by using soft tofu to make the cake.

684
00:28:57,535 --> 00:29:02,373
-So that the dish won't include any flour.
-Soft tofu to cake?

685
00:29:02,440 --> 00:29:04,676
I can call this
seaweed soup with soft tofu cake.

686
00:29:04,743 --> 00:29:06,111
POONG'S MASTERPIECE:
SEAWEED SOUP WITH SOFT TOFU CAKE

687
00:29:06,177 --> 00:29:09,247
You'll do that for the fridge owner
who doesn't enjoy flour.

688
00:29:09,314 --> 00:29:10,348
Are you paying homage?

689
00:29:10,415 --> 00:29:12,283
Yes, I'll challenge myself

690
00:29:12,350 --> 00:29:14,619
by cooking a dish that pays homage.

691
00:29:14,686 --> 00:29:18,123
If I may add,
if he'll make seaweed soup and blend it,

692
00:29:18,189 --> 00:29:19,324
it's downright copying.

693
00:29:19,390 --> 00:29:20,658
CTRL + C

694
00:29:20,725 --> 00:29:23,495
-I'm saying it's plagiarism.
-Yes.

695
00:29:23,561 --> 00:29:25,230
-In that case…
-He's appropriating.

696
00:29:25,296 --> 00:29:26,397
In that case

697
00:29:26,464 --> 00:29:28,233
I will copy them.

698
00:29:29,434 --> 00:29:31,569
ANNOUNCES PLAGIARISM

699
00:29:31,636 --> 00:29:33,271
He says he'll downright plagiarize.

700
00:29:33,338 --> 00:29:35,874
-Don't expect an homage. You're copying.
-Yes.

701
00:29:35,940 --> 00:29:38,209
Chef Kang-rok just laughed out loud.

702
00:29:38,276 --> 00:29:40,345
-He was funny.
-He was?

703
00:29:40,411 --> 00:29:42,847
If he finds it funny,
it must mean this is funny.

704
00:29:42,914 --> 00:29:45,550
Anyway, he seemed too shameless
for a guy who wants to plagiarize.

705
00:29:46,985 --> 00:29:49,087
If you can make it happen,

706
00:29:49,154 --> 00:29:52,223
I'm sure your fridge owner will be happy.

707
00:29:52,290 --> 00:29:55,360
And now, let us begin the cook-off
with ingredients from Hee-jun's fridge,

708
00:29:55,426 --> 00:29:59,497
and the order is,
"I want to taste the state of art."

709
00:30:03,401 --> 00:30:05,937
"Everything that goes through me
becomes art!"

710
00:30:06,004 --> 00:30:08,706
An expert fine-dining chef,
Chef Choi Hyun-suk!

711
00:30:08,773 --> 00:30:11,676
Is he brilliant or an eccentric?

712
00:30:11,743 --> 00:30:13,745
The performance artist
of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>,

713
00:30:13,812 --> 00:30:15,713
Webtoon artist Kim Poong is
up against him.

714
00:30:15,780 --> 00:30:19,617
Which one of them will stand tall
with a dish in the state of art?

715
00:30:19,684 --> 00:30:23,922
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

716
00:30:23,988 --> 00:30:26,491
I WANT TO TASTE STATE OF ART
KIM POONG VS CHOI HYUN-SUK

717
00:30:26,558 --> 00:30:28,226
The time is ticking.

718
00:30:28,293 --> 00:30:29,427
They begin right away.

719
00:30:29,494 --> 00:30:31,830
If Chef Hyun-suk shouts out the word stop,

720
00:30:31,896 --> 00:30:34,265
Poong cannot do anything for a minute.

721
00:30:34,332 --> 00:30:37,068
Please keep an eye out for that moment.

722
00:30:37,802 --> 00:30:40,004
-Did you chop up seaweed?
-Yes.

723
00:30:40,071 --> 00:30:42,574
Will you stir-fry the seaweed
before you boil them?

724
00:30:42,640 --> 00:30:43,675
Yes.

725
00:30:43,741 --> 00:30:45,109
He's using butter to fry those.

726
00:30:45,176 --> 00:30:46,311
Butter?

727
00:30:47,212 --> 00:30:49,113
He's cooking seaweed soup in a wok.

728
00:30:50,615 --> 00:30:52,350
3. MIX UNI, BROTH,
AND OYSTER SAUCE TO MAKE SEAWEED SOUP

729
00:30:52,417 --> 00:30:54,719
-I think he threw in sea urchin roe.
-I did.

730
00:30:55,687 --> 00:30:57,422
-I put it in.
-It'll be even creamier.

731
00:30:57,488 --> 00:30:59,858
Artist Poong is preparing seaweed soup

732
00:30:59,924 --> 00:31:03,027
because it's Hee-jun's favorite dish.

733
00:31:03,094 --> 00:31:05,997
I had told my wife that
I really wanted to try

734
00:31:06,064 --> 00:31:09,634
the flounder seaweed soup he made
on <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.

735
00:31:09,701 --> 00:31:12,837
It may be plagiarized,
but I'm glad I get to try it.

736
00:31:12,904 --> 00:31:14,672
-I see.
-I'm thrilled about that.

737
00:31:14,739 --> 00:31:17,242
It would've been better
if Chef Hyun-suk just made it.

738
00:31:17,308 --> 00:31:18,877
Mine could be more delicious.

739
00:31:18,943 --> 00:31:21,012
Mine could be more delicious!

740
00:31:21,579 --> 00:31:23,047
HMM

741
00:31:23,648 --> 00:31:26,050
CHOI HYUN-SUK PULLS OUT HIS DIET FOOD,
CUBED PORK TENDERLOIN

742
00:31:26,117 --> 00:31:27,418
Will he blend them?

743
00:31:27,485 --> 00:31:31,122
1. ADD CUBED PORK TENDERLOIN
AND SHRIMP MEAT INTO AN IMMERSION BLENDER

744
00:31:31,789 --> 00:31:33,191
Is that tonguefish?

745
00:31:33,258 --> 00:31:35,860
-This is Atka mackerel.
-Atka mackerel.

746
00:31:35,927 --> 00:31:37,862
He's skinning everything.

747
00:31:37,929 --> 00:31:39,731
That knife isn't his,

748
00:31:39,797 --> 00:31:42,066
-so he's having trouble skinning it.
-Yes.

749
00:31:42,133 --> 00:31:43,835
So that's Chef Ho-young's knife?

750
00:31:43,902 --> 00:31:46,404
Yes, it's mine,
so I hope he's gentle with it.

751
00:31:48,106 --> 00:31:50,008
Why are you skinning the fish?

752
00:31:50,074 --> 00:31:52,377
I plan to make tuile with the skin.

753
00:31:53,011 --> 00:31:54,245
You'll use it separately?

754
00:31:54,312 --> 00:31:57,949
Atka mackerel is known to have
delicious skin.

755
00:31:58,016 --> 00:32:00,285
It means he'll pay attention
to the presentation.

756
00:32:00,351 --> 00:32:02,186
He'll use both the skin and the meat.

757
00:32:02,253 --> 00:32:05,490
3. BLEND PORK, SHRIMP, ATKA MACKEREL,
EGG WHITES, STARCH, SALT TO MAKE MOUSSE

758
00:32:05,556 --> 00:32:08,760
He threw Atka mackerel in with egg whites
and starch, and began to blend it.

759
00:32:08,826 --> 00:32:11,329
MOUSSE COMPLETED

760
00:32:11,396 --> 00:32:12,864
TONGUEFISH IS IN THE PICTURE

761
00:32:12,931 --> 00:32:15,099
-There's tonguefish.
-That's tonguefish.

762
00:32:15,867 --> 00:32:18,770
That fish was half-dried,
so it's great even when it's just grilled.

763
00:32:18,836 --> 00:32:20,872
-That tonguefish?
-Yes.

764
00:32:20,939 --> 00:32:23,308
Chef Hyun-suk,
what will you do with the tonguefish?

765
00:32:23,374 --> 00:32:25,143
I'll wrap it around the mousse.

766
00:32:25,209 --> 00:32:27,912
HE'LL WRAP THE MOUSSE HE MADE
WITH TONGUEFISH MEAT

767
00:32:27,979 --> 00:32:30,348
4. SLICE THE TONGUEFISH
AND COAT IT WITH STARCH

768
00:32:31,716 --> 00:32:32,850
THE MOUSSE GOES INTO A PIPING BAG?

769
00:32:32,917 --> 00:32:35,920
Chef Hyun-suk puts it into a piping bag.

770
00:32:36,554 --> 00:32:38,856
-What's that step?
-My gosh.

771
00:32:39,724 --> 00:32:41,159
Why won't you answer me?

772
00:32:41,225 --> 00:32:44,162
You won't even answer us anymore.
Are you that nervous?

773
00:32:44,228 --> 00:32:45,930
I'm squeezing the mousse out.

774
00:32:45,997 --> 00:32:48,366
-To put it inside?
-He's wrapping it with the fish.

775
00:32:48,433 --> 00:32:50,601
So the wrap is tonguefish?

776
00:32:50,668 --> 00:32:51,536
It is.

777
00:32:52,570 --> 00:32:54,572
And he'll steam that?

778
00:32:54,639 --> 00:32:55,673
He's steaming it.

779
00:32:55,740 --> 00:32:56,941
-I see.
-It goes into a steamer.

780
00:32:57,008 --> 00:32:58,643
It'll be really tender once it's steamed.

781
00:32:58,710 --> 00:33:01,713
It could be a little dangerous
to mince half-dried fish

782
00:33:01,779 --> 00:33:03,614
and steam to cook it.

783
00:33:03,681 --> 00:33:06,150
-It may end up smelling fishy.
-That's right.

784
00:33:06,718 --> 00:33:08,953
How will he get rid of the smell?

785
00:33:09,020 --> 00:33:10,088
Do you like fishy food?

786
00:33:10,154 --> 00:33:11,823
I have a weak stomach.

787
00:33:11,889 --> 00:33:13,057
-Gosh.
-Oh, no.

788
00:33:13,124 --> 00:33:17,161
Chef Hyun-suk must be out of it.
Wait, you said you'd stop doing that!

789
00:33:17,228 --> 00:33:18,363
ADDING SALT AND COMEDY

790
00:33:18,429 --> 00:33:22,500
He said he'd stop doing
such performances, but he didn't.

791
00:33:22,567 --> 00:33:24,936
He threw in ground black pepper
as soon as he talked about fishy smell

792
00:33:25,003 --> 00:33:26,504
to get rid of the smell.

793
00:33:26,571 --> 00:33:30,441
HE BEGINS TO COPY EDWARD'S RICE CAKE

794
00:33:31,175 --> 00:33:33,778
Artist Poong, how will you make cake
with soft tofu?

795
00:33:33,845 --> 00:33:36,748
What's the white powder
under the soft tofu?

796
00:33:36,814 --> 00:33:38,282
-It's starch.
-Starch.

797
00:33:38,349 --> 00:33:40,518
It has no gluten,
so it's easy on your stomach.

798
00:33:41,185 --> 00:33:44,222
You can enjoy the cake
just by the taste of the tofu.

799
00:33:44,288 --> 00:33:47,158
I get that you'll turn it into cake,
but how will you use it?

800
00:33:47,225 --> 00:33:48,726
I'll take tiny balls

801
00:33:48,793 --> 00:33:52,497
and top off the seaweed soup with that.

802
00:33:52,563 --> 00:33:55,133
We shouldn't expect the texture
to be similar, right?

803
00:33:55,199 --> 00:33:57,301
It'll taste quite chewy,
just like rice cake.

804
00:33:57,368 --> 00:33:58,469
-Is that so?
-Yes.

805
00:33:58,536 --> 00:34:01,639
THE COOK OF THE DARKNESS
IN THE PROCESS OF COPYING

806
00:34:01,706 --> 00:34:04,008
He must have a secret.

807
00:34:05,476 --> 00:34:09,714
-He's currently using soft tofu to…
-It's getting glutinous.

808
00:34:09,781 --> 00:34:12,083
-My gosh.
-It's turning into something.

809
00:34:12,150 --> 00:34:13,718
-It looks like injeolmi.
-It gets glutinous.

810
00:34:13,785 --> 00:34:16,921
It looks like injeolmi.
After all, it must be rice cake.

811
00:34:16,988 --> 00:34:18,523
A SUCCESSFUL COPY

812
00:34:18,589 --> 00:34:19,424
I knew it.

813
00:34:19,490 --> 00:34:21,392
-He's stopping.
-That's the state of art.

814
00:34:21,459 --> 00:34:23,561
The rice cake is coming together.

815
00:34:23,628 --> 00:34:24,896
He did that with tofu.

816
00:34:24,962 --> 00:34:27,999
MOVING ON TO THE NEXT COPYCAT STEP

817
00:34:28,733 --> 00:34:30,968
HE THROWS THE SEAWEED SOUP INTO A BLENDER

818
00:34:31,536 --> 00:34:32,570
WHIRR

819
00:34:32,637 --> 00:34:34,839
-I've seen that somewhere.
-He's copying.

820
00:34:34,906 --> 00:34:36,674
-Plagiarism.
-Plagiarism.

821
00:34:36,741 --> 00:34:38,509
Is he blending the seaweed soup?

822
00:34:38,576 --> 00:34:40,945
-We've seen that a lot.
-We've seen it on <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.

823
00:34:41,012 --> 00:34:43,247
You're now watching
the process of plagiarism.

824
00:34:43,314 --> 00:34:45,349
-Thus far, he was a perfect copycat.
-Yes.

825
00:34:45,416 --> 00:34:47,718
7. ADD PASSION FRUIT PRESERVES,
TRUFFLE OIL, AND SALT TO MAKE SAUCE

826
00:34:47,785 --> 00:34:51,556
That's a jar of passion fruit preserves
we use to make tea.

827
00:34:51,622 --> 00:34:53,658
-He's using it like that?
-As sauce.

828
00:34:53,724 --> 00:34:55,760
He must be using it to make sauce.

829
00:34:55,827 --> 00:34:58,930
Will he cover the fishy smell
with the passion fruit sauce?

830
00:34:58,996 --> 00:35:01,199
-That might be the case.
-Yes.

831
00:35:01,866 --> 00:35:04,235
8. RUB SOY SAUCE ON ATKA MACKEREL SKIN
AND COAT WITH STARCH

832
00:35:04,302 --> 00:35:06,204
He's trying to deep-fry the skin

833
00:35:06,270 --> 00:35:07,705
to make it crunchy.

834
00:35:09,640 --> 00:35:12,677
-He's coating Atka mackerel skin to fry?
-Yes.

835
00:35:12,743 --> 00:35:14,479
HE EVEN PULLS OUT A THERMOMETER

836
00:35:14,545 --> 00:35:17,215
I guess you're looking for
a suitable temperature.

837
00:35:17,281 --> 00:35:20,218
-I was thinking around 180 degrees.
-Around 180 degrees.

838
00:35:22,453 --> 00:35:26,958
-Wait, the bamboo mat…
-Wait!

839
00:35:27,458 --> 00:35:30,094
He's frying something inside that mat.

840
00:35:30,161 --> 00:35:31,863
WILL THE SKIN GET FRIED WELL?

841
00:35:31,929 --> 00:35:33,631
You have eight minutes left.

842
00:35:33,698 --> 00:35:38,636
Chef Hyun-suk, you can't use the stop perk
in about two minutes.

843
00:35:38,703 --> 00:35:40,538
Strainer.

844
00:35:40,605 --> 00:35:43,508
COPYCAT POONG WANTS TO STRAIN THE SOUP

845
00:35:43,574 --> 00:35:45,309
-I doubt he'll use it.
-Right?

846
00:35:45,376 --> 00:35:47,278
He's busy doing his own thing.

847
00:35:47,345 --> 00:35:48,880
And he's fighting against Poong.

848
00:35:48,946 --> 00:35:50,515
He only said he'd use it.

849
00:35:50,581 --> 00:35:54,218
-Wait, stop.
-Stop! Poong, stop!

850
00:35:54,285 --> 00:35:57,088
-You can't move for a minute.
-Wait.

851
00:35:57,155 --> 00:36:00,258
-Stop.
-Stop! Poong, stop!

852
00:36:00,324 --> 00:36:03,227
-You can't move for a minute.
-Wait.

853
00:36:03,294 --> 00:36:05,196
You can't stay stop now.

854
00:36:05,263 --> 00:36:07,665
-Oh, no.
-Poong, stop.

855
00:36:07,732 --> 00:36:09,567
Kim Poong cannot cook anymore.

856
00:36:09,634 --> 00:36:12,170
-He used this on me?
-He used it.

857
00:36:12,970 --> 00:36:14,338
Chef Hyun-suk uses this perk.

858
00:36:14,405 --> 00:36:16,040
I could never even imagine.

859
00:36:16,107 --> 00:36:19,610
He doesn't care if it's Poong.
He'll stop him for a minute.

860
00:36:20,178 --> 00:36:23,147
9. ADD BUTTER TO THE SAUCE AND MELT IT

861
00:36:23,214 --> 00:36:25,616
HE MOVES QUICKLY
AFTER GIVING HIS OPPONENT A PENALTY

862
00:36:25,683 --> 00:36:29,020
Chef Hyun-suk uses truffle oil.

863
00:36:29,086 --> 00:36:31,989
The fridge owner loves truffle oil.

864
00:36:32,557 --> 00:36:34,692
DRIPPING

865
00:36:34,759 --> 00:36:36,327
READ THE ROOM

866
00:36:36,394 --> 00:36:37,528
SHAKING

867
00:36:37,595 --> 00:36:38,930
Poong, you can't shake that.

868
00:36:38,996 --> 00:36:41,933
-No, I'm not doing it.
-You aren't?

869
00:36:41,999 --> 00:36:43,668
He's shaking his head.

870
00:36:43,734 --> 00:36:44,969
He has a hand tremor issue.

871
00:36:45,036 --> 00:36:46,404
He's just cold.

872
00:36:46,470 --> 00:36:48,072
I had always been like this.

873
00:36:48,139 --> 00:36:50,608
-I always had hand tremor.
-Come on.

874
00:36:50,675 --> 00:36:52,910
WHAT AN AMAZING TRICK

875
00:36:52,977 --> 00:36:54,912
-Stop drinking so much.
-When did you develop that?

876
00:36:54,979 --> 00:36:57,515
-He had a bit too much to drink.
-Is that so?

877
00:36:57,582 --> 00:37:01,018
You have ten seconds left, Poong.

878
00:37:01,085 --> 00:37:03,654
He actually used this perk
on Kim Poong.

879
00:37:03,721 --> 00:37:04,755
What was that?

880
00:37:05,489 --> 00:37:06,591
Okay. Three.

881
00:37:06,657 --> 00:37:08,526
Two. One.

882
00:37:08,593 --> 00:37:10,194
-Poong, you can move again.
-Darn it.

883
00:37:10,261 --> 00:37:12,697
THE PERK ENDS

884
00:37:12,763 --> 00:37:15,166
Chef Hyun-suk uses the perk on Poong.

885
00:37:15,233 --> 00:37:16,834
-He used this on me?
-Yes.

886
00:37:16,901 --> 00:37:19,270
-Gosh.
-Poong is in disadvantage now.

887
00:37:19,337 --> 00:37:23,374
Hee-jun, it may be a copycat recipe,
but it looks delicious.

888
00:37:23,441 --> 00:37:25,676
I think Artist Poong may be
a bit in a rush.

889
00:37:25,743 --> 00:37:27,445
You have five minutes and 30 seconds.

890
00:37:27,511 --> 00:37:31,048
His cooking improved a lot
compared to five years ago.

891
00:37:32,116 --> 00:37:36,187
But I hope he rises above
the copycat level.

892
00:37:36,921 --> 00:37:39,457
-He's freezing the batter.
-It's to give it more texture.

893
00:37:39,523 --> 00:37:41,492
The batter is now in iced water.

894
00:37:42,426 --> 00:37:46,163
There's Atka mackerel skin
inside the bamboo mat.

895
00:37:46,230 --> 00:37:47,765
Atka mackerel skin.

896
00:37:47,832 --> 00:37:50,368
Why did you wrap it in the bamboo mat?

897
00:37:50,434 --> 00:37:53,671
If I didn't do that,
it would've curled up.

898
00:37:53,738 --> 00:37:55,506
Curling up? It was because of the shape.

899
00:37:55,573 --> 00:37:59,043
-He wanted to keep it in shape.
-You're right.

900
00:37:59,110 --> 00:38:01,445
-Sung-ju, please make a report over there.
-Yes?

901
00:38:01,512 --> 00:38:04,515
-We have five minutes. Yes.
-Shall I? I'll report out on the field.

902
00:38:04,582 --> 00:38:06,884
Here's the situation out on the field.

903
00:38:06,951 --> 00:38:08,719
Choi Hyun-suk versus Kim Poong.

904
00:38:08,786 --> 00:38:10,354
He's picking up the steamer.

905
00:38:10,421 --> 00:38:13,391
The steamer had that thing
he put together before.

906
00:38:13,457 --> 00:38:15,026
-He made just one.
-Yes, just one.

907
00:38:15,092 --> 00:38:17,061
-It looks good.
-I hope it went well.

908
00:38:17,128 --> 00:38:20,131
He said he'd use passion fruit
to make the sauce.

909
00:38:20,197 --> 00:38:22,667
So can you taste it and see
if it can cover up the fishy smell?

910
00:38:22,733 --> 00:38:24,435
It looks scorching hot.

911
00:38:24,502 --> 00:38:25,670
You still need to taste it.

912
00:38:26,704 --> 00:38:27,972
May I try this one first?

913
00:38:28,039 --> 00:38:29,173
Check if it's been copied well.

914
00:38:29,240 --> 00:38:31,609
-All right.
-Has he plagiarized the right way?

915
00:38:31,676 --> 00:38:33,444
This is the seaweed soup broth.

916
00:38:33,511 --> 00:38:35,780
-Please taste this first.
-Why?

917
00:38:36,847 --> 00:38:38,382
-It looks hot.
-Come on.

918
00:38:39,350 --> 00:38:40,885
SMACKING

919
00:38:41,485 --> 00:38:43,321
Will the sauce get the smell out?

920
00:38:43,387 --> 00:38:45,890
HOW DOES THE SAUCE TASTE?

921
00:38:46,590 --> 00:38:49,327
It's what I call fine dining.

922
00:38:49,393 --> 00:38:51,595
KEEPING A STRAIGHT FACE

923
00:38:51,662 --> 00:38:53,664
It's what I call fine dining.

924
00:38:53,731 --> 00:38:56,133
A man in the fine-dining business,
Choi Hyun-suk.

925
00:38:56,767 --> 00:38:58,569
-It looks pretty.
-It tastes tangy.

926
00:38:58,636 --> 00:38:59,870
Will it cover up the fish smell?

927
00:38:59,937 --> 00:39:02,440
-I think it will do that.
-Okay.

928
00:39:02,506 --> 00:39:04,141
-All right.
-Have a taste of that.

929
00:39:04,208 --> 00:39:06,577
This is the dish Artist Poong made.

930
00:39:06,644 --> 00:39:09,880
-Okay.
-This is Artist Poong's seaweed soup.

931
00:39:10,815 --> 00:39:11,982
You have three minutes.

932
00:39:12,717 --> 00:39:18,456
Is it a masterpiece? Or is it a knockoff?

933
00:39:19,724 --> 00:39:21,792
It's a knockoff.

934
00:39:21,859 --> 00:39:23,594
-Darn it.
-It's a knockoff.

935
00:39:24,762 --> 00:39:26,230
-Is it too salty?
-It's too bland.

936
00:39:26,297 --> 00:39:27,798
-Is it? Okay.
-It's too bland.

937
00:39:27,865 --> 00:39:30,167
-You can't do this. It's too bland.
-"You can't do this."

938
00:39:30,234 --> 00:39:31,769
-I like bland-tasting food.
-I see.

939
00:39:31,836 --> 00:39:33,003
Hee-jun enjoys bland food.

940
00:39:33,070 --> 00:39:35,039
I thought it could get salty.

941
00:39:35,106 --> 00:39:38,242
It tastes a bit bland
and I smell a bit of fishy seaweed smell.

942
00:39:38,309 --> 00:39:39,643
I can't handle the fishy smell.

943
00:39:39,710 --> 00:39:40,945
You have to handle the smell.

944
00:39:41,011 --> 00:39:43,948
-Shouldn't you throw sugar in?
-No, I'm fine.

945
00:39:44,682 --> 00:39:46,617
CHOI HYUN-SUK CHOPS
THE DEEP-FRIED ATKA MACKEREL SKIN

946
00:39:46,684 --> 00:39:47,852
It sounds crunchy.

947
00:39:50,988 --> 00:39:55,292
HE CAREFULLY TOPS IT WITH THE TUILE

948
00:39:56,727 --> 00:40:03,701
HE PASSIONATELY SHOWS HIS ARTISTIC SIDE
BY SPRINKLING RED PEPPER ON TOP

949
00:40:03,768 --> 00:40:05,970
It's hot. You didn't even turn this off.

950
00:40:06,036 --> 00:40:07,004
He's done!

951
00:40:07,071 --> 00:40:09,740
CHOI HYUN-SUK FINISHES
I HAVE GOT TONGUEFISH

952
00:40:09,807 --> 00:40:12,276
It's hot. You didn't even turn this off.
