the nutty sticky rice smell.

1181
00:49:40,811 --> 00:49:42,079
I was really shocked.

1182
00:49:42,145 --> 00:49:44,481
So let me evaluate the dish.

1183
00:49:44,548 --> 00:49:46,583
-He said he'd copy me, right?
-Yes.

1184
00:49:46,650 --> 00:49:49,386
-He managed to copy my dear Kyun.
-I see.

1185
00:49:49,453 --> 00:49:51,054
But he failed to copy me.

1186
00:49:53,657 --> 00:49:54,591
The soup was different.

1187
00:49:54,658 --> 00:49:59,529
He couldn't copy Choi Hyun-suk's recipe,
so this dish was nothing but a knockoff.

1188
00:49:59,596 --> 00:50:01,898
Now, that's all for the day.

1189
00:50:01,965 --> 00:50:04,868
-You're to make the decision.
-Okay.

1190
00:50:04,935 --> 00:50:08,238
Press one for Kim Poong,
and press two for Choi Hyun-suk.

1191
00:50:08,305 --> 00:50:11,074
-Yes, I pressed one.
-You did? Okay.

1192
00:50:11,141 --> 00:50:12,943
Did Hee-jun pick

1193
00:50:13,010 --> 00:50:15,112
Artist Poong's dish?

1194
00:50:15,178 --> 00:50:17,981
Or did he pick Chef Hyun-suk's dish?

1195
00:50:18,048 --> 00:50:20,417
Who will be the leader?

1196
00:50:20,484 --> 00:50:23,020
Who cooked in the state of the art?

1197
00:50:23,687 --> 00:50:26,156
-What is Hee-jun's choice?
-What is it?

1198
00:50:26,223 --> 00:50:28,859
-What is Hee-jun's choice?
-What is it?

1199
00:50:28,925 --> 00:50:30,560
Who is it?

1200
00:50:31,194 --> 00:50:32,863
Which taste did he want more?

1201
00:50:33,430 --> 00:50:36,299
Who is it? Which taste did he want more?

1202
00:50:36,366 --> 00:50:38,101
CHOI HYUN-SUK WINS

1203
00:50:38,168 --> 00:50:40,637
CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK'S
I HAVE GOT TONGUEFISH WINS

1204
00:50:40,704 --> 00:50:42,072
-Choi Hyun-suk.
-Chef Hyun-suk.

1205
00:50:42,139 --> 00:50:43,774
Chef Hyun-suk wins.

1206
00:50:43,840 --> 00:50:45,942
I knew it.

1207
00:50:46,009 --> 00:50:49,813
I suddenly felt inexplicably moved.

1208
00:50:49,880 --> 00:50:53,450
It seemed like the first time
I tried a dish with layers of flavors.

1209
00:50:53,517 --> 00:50:54,584
-I see.
-Yes.

1210
00:50:54,651 --> 00:50:56,653
Joong-ki, if you had a choice,
who would you have picked?

1211
00:50:56,720 --> 00:50:59,456
-My gosh.
-"My gosh."

1212
00:50:59,956 --> 00:51:02,259
-This is hard.
-It is.

1213
00:51:02,325 --> 00:51:04,828
-I would've chosen Artist Poong.
-Kim Poong.

1214
00:51:05,395 --> 00:51:08,532
-He stole Joong-ki's heart.
-He did.

1215
00:51:08,598 --> 00:51:10,767
I also love seaweed soup a lot,

1216
00:51:10,834 --> 00:51:15,772
and it also had this chewy
ongsimi-like tofu cake.

1217
00:51:15,839 --> 00:51:18,442
How did he do that with soft tofu?

1218
00:51:18,508 --> 00:51:20,210
He seems like a genius.

1219
00:51:20,277 --> 00:51:23,747
Chef Hyun-suk wins twice in a row.

1220
00:51:23,814 --> 00:51:26,183
He's the first chef to get two stars.

1221
00:51:26,249 --> 00:51:28,118
He has two wins!

1222
00:51:28,185 --> 00:51:30,687
I HAVE GOT TONGUEFISH
BY CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK

1223
00:51:30,754 --> 00:51:33,256
THE RECIPE

1224
00:51:33,323 --> 00:51:37,494
The second round
with Hee-jun's fridge will be held

1225
00:51:37,561 --> 00:51:41,698
between the Master of Chinese Cuisine
and the Goddess of Chinese Cuisine.

1226
00:51:41,765 --> 00:51:44,701
Last time, Chef Eun-yeong

1227
00:51:44,768 --> 00:51:49,306
already defeated Kim Poong,
Chef Yeon-bok's best pupil,

1228
00:51:49,372 --> 00:51:53,910
and wanted to challenge Chef Yeon-bok
if she got a chance.

1229
00:51:53,977 --> 00:51:56,379
She has shared that ambition with us.

1230
00:51:56,446 --> 00:51:59,382
And that match came right away.

1231
00:51:59,449 --> 00:52:01,685
Chef Yeon-bok, how do you feel?

1232
00:52:01,751 --> 00:52:04,721
I think she's a little too early.

1233
00:52:04,788 --> 00:52:05,889
YOU HAVE A WHILE TO GO, KID

1234
00:52:06,389 --> 00:52:08,258
She needs to take smaller steps.

1235
00:52:08,325 --> 00:52:10,093
I hoped she would do that,

1236
00:52:10,160 --> 00:52:12,562
-but she came at me right away.
-She did.

1237
00:52:12,629 --> 00:52:16,867
Last week, I said
I wanted to challenge Chef Yeon-bok.

1238
00:52:16,933 --> 00:52:19,736
And last week, he made 2 dishes
within 15 minutes, right?

1239
00:52:19,803 --> 00:52:22,339
-Yes.
-I was a bit shocked as I watched.

1240
00:52:22,405 --> 00:52:24,040
I thought it wouldn't be embarrassing

1241
00:52:24,107 --> 00:52:25,942
even if I end up without stars

1242
00:52:26,009 --> 00:52:28,011
and don't add a star to my collection.

1243
00:52:28,078 --> 00:52:32,048
It seems like you're thinking
that you'll probably lose this round.

1244
00:52:32,115 --> 00:52:33,316
That's not true.

1245
00:52:33,383 --> 00:52:35,285
The future of Chinese cuisine

1246
00:52:35,352 --> 00:52:38,288
can change completely
after this round today.

1247
00:52:38,355 --> 00:52:39,556
I look forward to this.

1248
00:52:40,056 --> 00:52:42,659
What's important is

1249
00:52:42,726 --> 00:52:45,128
that Hee-jun isn't the type

1250
00:52:45,195 --> 00:52:47,130
who enjoys Chinese-style dishes.

1251
00:52:47,197 --> 00:52:51,134
But I really want to try Dongpo pork.

1252
00:52:51,201 --> 00:52:53,170
MAKE DONGPO PORK NOW?

1253
00:52:53,837 --> 00:52:55,539
Can you do that in 15 minutes?

1254
00:52:55,605 --> 00:52:57,941
I don't think you can do that.

1255
00:52:58,008 --> 00:52:59,910
-Dongpo pork in 15 minutes?
-Can it happen?

1256
00:52:59,976 --> 00:53:02,345
Even Joong-ki shook his head now.

1257
00:53:02,412 --> 00:53:04,681
-Isn't it too harsh to ask for that now?
-No.

1258
00:53:04,748 --> 00:53:06,349
I didn't mean I wanted it now.

1259
00:53:06,416 --> 00:53:08,852
-You don't have the ingredients, either.
-I don't.

1260
00:53:08,919 --> 00:53:10,887
-All I have is the thin pork belly.
-Exactly.

1261
00:53:10,954 --> 00:53:13,924
You don't have the ingredients,
but you keep talking about it.

1262
00:53:13,990 --> 00:53:17,594
We can't make miracles just like that.

1263
00:53:17,661 --> 00:53:20,764
My place needs six hours
to make Dongpo pork.

1264
00:53:20,830 --> 00:53:23,700
If he can't do it in 15 minutes,
then no one can.

1265
00:53:23,767 --> 00:53:24,968
-No.
-No.

1266
00:53:25,035 --> 00:53:27,470
-Please give up on the Dongpo pork.
-Okay.

1267
00:53:27,537 --> 00:53:29,339
But I am curious.

1268
00:53:29,406 --> 00:53:31,274
I rarely eat Chinese because of flour,

1269
00:53:31,341 --> 00:53:35,278
but I'll get to eat dishes
made by the masters of Chinese cuisine.

1270
00:53:35,345 --> 00:53:37,581
-I'm excited.
-I see.

1271
00:53:37,647 --> 00:53:41,218
Now, will you use your perk or not?

1272
00:53:41,284 --> 00:53:43,453
-Let's find out.
-Yes, right.

1273
00:53:43,520 --> 00:53:46,456
Master Yeon-bok has such fast hands,

1274
00:53:46,523 --> 00:53:50,694
so I believe he'll do a great job
even if I stop him for a minute.

1275
00:53:50,760 --> 00:53:52,162
I see.

1276
00:53:52,229 --> 00:53:55,232
The new chefs are having fun
with the one-minute stop.

1277
00:53:55,298 --> 00:53:56,199
-It's a big deal.
-Yes.

1278
00:53:57,033 --> 00:53:59,369
CHEF LEE YEON-BOK'S INGREDIENTS:
PICKLED GREEN ONION, SOFT TOFU, CAPSICUM,

1279
00:53:59,436 --> 00:54:01,738
LAO GAN MA, SOYA NOODLES, NAPA CABBAGE,
OCTOPUS, SHRIMP, PEANUT BUTTER, LETTUCE

1280
00:54:01,805 --> 00:54:04,741
The dish I'll make today is YNF.

1281
00:54:04,808 --> 00:54:06,209
-YNF?
-YNF?

1282
00:54:06,276 --> 00:54:07,577
YNF.

1283
00:54:07,644 --> 00:54:10,780
Yeon-bok's Noodles tossed in Fire.

1284
00:54:10,847 --> 00:54:12,816
-I see.
-I see.

1285
00:54:12,882 --> 00:54:14,417
-Noodles?
-Hee-jun said

1286
00:54:14,484 --> 00:54:15,785
-he hated noodles.
-Yes.

1287
00:54:15,852 --> 00:54:18,488
I saw soya noodles in his fridge.

1288
00:54:18,555 --> 00:54:21,358
-This is something…
-Yes, soya noodles?

1289
00:54:21,424 --> 00:54:23,226
One of the signature dishes

1290
00:54:23,293 --> 00:54:25,195
-at my restaurant is dandan noodles.
-Dandan noodles.

1291
00:54:25,262 --> 00:54:28,231
I'll make dandan noodles.
And because you like octopus and shrimp,

1292
00:54:28,298 --> 00:54:31,701
I'll stir-fry it with veggies

1293
00:54:31,768 --> 00:54:33,603
and top it on the noodles.

1294
00:54:33,670 --> 00:54:35,305
You're only using seafood?

1295
00:54:35,372 --> 00:54:36,806
Yes, only seafood.
I listened to everything.

1296
00:54:36,873 --> 00:54:39,809
He doesn't like meat,
but seafood and vegetables.

1297
00:54:39,876 --> 00:54:41,811
And he said he liked peanut butter.

1298
00:54:41,878 --> 00:54:42,979
I wanted to cook with that mix.

1299
00:54:43,046 --> 00:54:45,615
I've never seen peanut butter
used in a dish.

1300
00:54:45,682 --> 00:54:47,617
Yes, he has peanut butter.

1301
00:54:47,684 --> 00:54:50,587
One of my signature menus is
also braised napa cabbage.

1302
00:54:50,654 --> 00:54:52,122
Braised napa cabbage and soft tofu.

1303
00:54:52,188 --> 00:54:56,860
You have to make all 3 dishes
in just 14 minutes, including the stop.

1304
00:54:56,926 --> 00:54:59,729
-Gosh, yes.
-And it's a minute in the middle.

1305
00:54:59,796 --> 00:55:01,298
You should think about that.

1306
00:55:01,364 --> 00:55:03,900
Anyway, depending on the situation,
he may skip it.

1307
00:55:03,967 --> 00:55:04,901
He could skip it.

1308
00:55:04,968 --> 00:55:07,804
-No, I'll make three dishes.
-He will.

1309
00:55:07,871 --> 00:55:10,373
-He's a chef.
-It's me, Lee Yeon-bok.

1310
00:55:10,940 --> 00:55:13,376
HE'S SO COOL
AS THE MASTER OF CHINESE CUISINE

1311
00:55:13,443 --> 00:55:15,912
Lee Yeon-bok is prominent
in Chinese cuisine.

1312
00:55:16,746 --> 00:55:19,082
CHEF PARK EUN-YEONG'S INGREDIENTS:
SHIITAKE MUSHROOM, BAY LEAVES,

1313
00:55:19,149 --> 00:55:21,451
SHRIMP, NAPA CABBAGE,
THIN PORK BELLY, TRUFFLE OIL, OYSTER SAUCE

1314
00:55:21,518 --> 00:55:23,887
The dish I prepared today is

1315
00:55:23,953 --> 00:55:25,789
Dongpo Pork Meringue Dumplings.

1316
00:55:25,855 --> 00:55:28,458
-Dongpo Pork Meringue Dumplings.
-Dongpo Pork Meringue Dumplings.

1317
00:55:28,525 --> 00:55:32,896
We heard Dongpo pork,
dumplings, and meringue too.

1318
00:55:32,962 --> 00:55:34,064
What's your dish like?

1319
00:55:34,130 --> 00:55:35,965
I received a lot of attention

1320
00:55:36,032 --> 00:55:38,735
after making Dongpo pork dumplings
on <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.

1321
00:55:38,802 --> 00:55:42,005
Hee-jun just said he wanted to try it,

1322
00:55:42,072 --> 00:55:44,541
but he also had trouble digesting flour,

1323
00:55:44,607 --> 00:55:47,644
so I'll use meringue as the dumpling skin.

1324
00:55:47,711 --> 00:55:50,046
I'll use meringue instead of flour

1325
00:55:50,113 --> 00:55:51,381
-to make dumplings.
-Can she do that?

1326
00:55:51,448 --> 00:55:53,483
She's using meringue
instead of dumpling skin?

1327
00:55:53,550 --> 00:55:54,751
-Yes.
-Dumplings.

1328
00:55:54,818 --> 00:55:57,620
Hee-jun had been dying to try Dongpo pork.

1329
00:55:57,687 --> 00:55:59,122
What's meringue?

1330
00:55:59,189 --> 00:56:00,323
Meringue?

1331
00:56:00,390 --> 00:56:03,159
It's the substance you get when you whip

1332
00:56:03,226 --> 00:56:05,695
-just the egg whites and make it firm.
-Like foam?

1333
00:56:05,762 --> 00:56:07,597
It's often used for dessert,

1334
00:56:07,664 --> 00:56:10,700
-so I look forward to seeing her at work.
-Right?

1335
00:56:10,767 --> 00:56:14,037
And there were no ingredients
for Dongpo pork. What will you use?

1336
00:56:14,104 --> 00:56:15,972
I want to stir-fry the meat,

1337
00:56:16,039 --> 00:56:19,476
add soy sauce and oyster sauce,
and make a quick version of it.

1338
00:56:19,542 --> 00:56:20,510
I see.

1339
00:56:21,544 --> 00:56:22,746
I can't imagine what it'll be like.

1340
00:56:22,812 --> 00:56:25,281
You might end up crying again.

1341
00:56:25,782 --> 00:56:28,918
Let us begin

1342
00:56:28,985 --> 00:56:32,922
the must-eat restaurants round
with Hee-jun's ingredients.

1343
00:56:32,989 --> 00:56:34,991
Chef Park Eun-yeong is here

1344
00:56:35,058 --> 00:56:37,093
to conquer Chef Lee Yeon-bok,

1345
00:56:37,160 --> 00:56:41,431
a longtime rival to her teacher,
Lu Chinglai, with her youthful vigor.

1346
00:56:41,498 --> 00:56:44,134
She's up against
an experienced master of 52 years

1347
00:56:44,200 --> 00:56:47,137
who'll put her back to her place,

1348
00:56:47,203 --> 00:56:49,606
Chef Lee Yeon-bok.

1349
00:56:49,672 --> 00:56:53,276
Will there be a change in generations
in the realm of Chinese cuisine?

1350
00:56:53,343 --> 00:56:57,080
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

1351
00:56:57,147 --> 00:56:59,949
HIGH EXPECTATIONS

1352
00:57:00,016 --> 00:57:01,718
Begin!

1353
00:57:01,785 --> 00:57:04,454
THE OLD AND THE NEW ROUND
OF CHINESE CUISINE

1354
00:57:05,789 --> 00:57:07,857
I know Chef Yeon-bok cooks quickly,

1355
00:57:07,924 --> 00:57:10,493
-but can he make three dishes?
-I wonder.

1356
00:57:10,560 --> 00:57:13,963
It may happen without the one-minute stop,
but he will get stopped.

1357
00:57:14,030 --> 00:57:16,499
-When will she stop him?
-Right.

1358
00:57:18,067 --> 00:57:20,103
PARK EUN-YEONG ATTACKS FIRST
WITH NAPA CABBAGE

1359
00:57:20,670 --> 00:57:22,672
LEE YEON-BOK FIGHTS BACK
ALSO WITH NAPA CABBAGE!

1360
00:57:22,739 --> 00:57:24,908
They're both cutting napa cabbage.

1361
00:57:24,974 --> 00:57:28,278
They're both working on napa cabbage.

1362
00:57:28,344 --> 00:57:30,747
PARK EUN-YEONG DICES IT

1363
00:57:30,814 --> 00:57:33,716
1. DICE NAPA CABBAGE
AND DRAW WATER OUT BY USING SALT

1364
00:57:33,783 --> 00:57:35,585
What's Chef Yeon-bok doing?

1365
00:57:35,652 --> 00:57:37,787
-Tofu.
-Soft tofu.

1366
00:57:37,854 --> 00:57:39,189
He's using tofu.

1367
00:57:39,255 --> 00:57:41,157
-Yes.
-I see.

1368
00:57:41,858 --> 00:57:45,094
He's making stir-fried noodles,
seafood stir fry, and braised cabbage.

1369
00:57:45,161 --> 00:57:47,630
He puts tofu between the cabbage.

1370
00:57:47,697 --> 00:57:49,132
You'll just steam it like that?

1371
00:57:49,199 --> 00:57:50,767
1. STEAM CABBAGE
WITH SOFT TOFU IN THE MIDDLE

1372
00:57:50,834 --> 00:57:52,802
-I see.
-Whoa.

1373
00:57:52,869 --> 00:57:54,471
He'll steam it like that?

1374
00:57:54,537 --> 00:57:56,172
WESTERN CUISINE CHEFS FIND IT FASCINATING

1375
00:57:56,239 --> 00:57:58,441
Doesn't soft tofu get mushy
when it's steamed?

1376
00:57:58,508 --> 00:58:00,143
-It does.
-Exactly.

1377
00:58:00,210 --> 00:58:02,245
-It does get mushy with heat.
-Yes.

1378
00:58:02,312 --> 00:58:04,747
It can't take the weight
and becomes a mush.

1379
00:58:04,814 --> 00:58:07,283
-There's the octopus.
-Octopus.

1380
00:58:07,350 --> 00:58:11,120
If you cook octopus well,
it'll taste chewy and delicious.

1381
00:58:11,187 --> 00:58:13,857
-I love octopus.
-He loves it, and he called it adorable.

1382
00:58:13,923 --> 00:58:16,159
He doesn't find it gross.

1383
00:58:16,226 --> 00:58:17,760
PARK EUN-YEONG FIGHTS BACK WITH SHRIMP

1384
00:58:17,827 --> 00:58:19,796
Chef Eun-yeong uses shrimp.

1385
00:58:19,863 --> 00:58:21,064
THE SHRIMP IS STICKING

1386
00:58:21,698 --> 00:58:23,366
PUSHES AND PUTS THEM DOWN

1387
00:58:24,634 --> 00:58:25,902
He's using shrimp too.

1388
00:58:26,970 --> 00:58:28,705
He said he liked seafood.

1389
00:58:28,771 --> 00:58:31,641
Yes, Chef Yeon-bok is
working on its sides.

1390
00:58:31,708 --> 00:58:33,510
PARK EUN-YEONG MINCES THEM

1391
00:58:33,576 --> 00:58:35,545
2. GET OCTOPUS AND SHRIMP READY

1392
00:58:36,145 --> 00:58:38,314
HER MAIN INGREDIENT: THIN PORK BELLY

1393
00:58:38,381 --> 00:58:40,083
Chef Eun-yeong uses thin pork belly.

1394
00:58:40,149 --> 00:58:43,553
-This will become Dongpo pork.
-How will she do that?

1395
00:58:43,620 --> 00:58:47,190
How will she make
Dongpo pork with thin pork belly?

1396
00:58:47,257 --> 00:58:50,560
Chinese chefs
usually get everything ready first,

1397
00:58:50,627 --> 00:58:52,462
-then they get cooking.
-Yes.

1398
00:58:52,529 --> 00:58:54,464
GETTING THE VEGGIES READY!

1399
00:58:54,531 --> 00:58:55,832
CHOPPING ONIONS

1400
00:58:55,899 --> 00:58:59,302
You're now seeing him chopping
with the Chinese kitchen knife.

1401
00:58:59,369 --> 00:59:02,338
Hee-jun is watching him and thinking,
"He's making a dish for me."

1402
00:59:02,405 --> 00:59:05,542
He's about to get teary-eyed.

1403
00:59:05,608 --> 00:59:06,643
Thank you so much.

1404
00:59:06,709 --> 00:59:08,811
Chef Eun-yeong cuts green onion.

1405
00:59:08,878 --> 00:59:10,313
CHOPPING GREEN ONION

1406
00:59:10,380 --> 00:59:13,483
Joong-ki is taking a video.

1407
00:59:13,550 --> 00:59:18,288
Joong-ki is taking a video
of Chef Eun-yeong chopping green onion.

1408
00:59:20,690 --> 00:59:23,560
-This time, capsicum.
-Capsicum!

1409
00:59:23,626 --> 00:59:25,428
Are you chopping? I will chop too.

1410
00:59:25,495 --> 00:59:26,496
HEHE

1411
00:59:26,563 --> 00:59:28,998
Their knives are dancing on the board.

1412
00:59:29,065 --> 00:59:30,733
-They don't even spare a moment.
-No.

1413
00:59:30,800 --> 00:59:33,202
EUN-YEONG REPLIES WITH HER KNIFE

1414
00:59:33,269 --> 00:59:34,771
If you chop, I'll chop too.

1415
00:59:34,837 --> 00:59:38,074
It feels like a Nanta performance,
they exchange the chopping sound.

1416
00:59:38,141 --> 00:59:42,478
Can you salsa dance to this rhythm?

1417
00:59:43,112 --> 00:59:45,682
HE SMOOTHLY ASKS FOR SOMETHING TOO MUCH

1418
00:59:45,748 --> 00:59:46,616
Can you salsa?

1419
00:59:47,584 --> 00:59:48,851
I ALSO CAN'T DO THAT

1420
00:59:49,586 --> 00:59:50,987
-I guess not.
-No.

1421
00:59:51,054 --> 00:59:53,556
This rhythm does not go with salsa dance.

1422
00:59:53,623 --> 00:59:57,594
I think it could happen. The salsa moves.

1423
00:59:57,660 --> 00:59:58,928
FUN PREPARATION WITH SALSA!

1424
00:59:58,995 --> 01:00:00,396
RHYTHMIC BEAT

1425
01:00:00,463 --> 01:00:01,764
MORE RHYTHM

1426
01:00:01,831 --> 01:00:03,800
BAM

1427
01:00:04,634 --> 01:00:06,002
-He slams it down.
-Yes.

1428
01:00:06,069 --> 01:00:08,271
They continue to cut.

1429
01:00:08,338 --> 01:00:10,640
WE AREN'T COOKING, WE'RE IN RHYTHM

1430
01:00:10,707 --> 01:00:13,643
This is art. This is seriously art.

1431
01:00:14,210 --> 01:00:15,144
PARK EUN-YEONG IS DONE

1432
01:00:15,211 --> 01:00:18,214
Chef Yeon-bok is
still busy preparing ingredients.

1433
01:00:18,281 --> 01:00:19,282
Raw garlic cloves.

1434
01:00:19,349 --> 01:00:22,385
He's been preparing ingredients
for over four minutes now.

1435
01:00:22,452 --> 01:00:23,686
-Yes.
-It's been four minutes?

1436
01:00:23,753 --> 01:00:26,990
-Already?
-Yes, and he hasn't started cooking.

1437
01:00:27,056 --> 01:00:30,159
The preparation always takes a long time
in Chinese cuisine,

1438
01:00:30,226 --> 01:00:31,694
but the cooking process is quick.

1439
01:00:31,761 --> 01:00:36,232
She just put thin pork belly on the pan.

1440
01:00:36,299 --> 01:00:39,268
I hope this tastes like Dongpo pork.

1441
01:00:40,303 --> 01:00:43,106
She threw in shrimps,
pork, and green onion.

1442
01:00:43,172 --> 01:00:46,209
SEASON WITH OYSTER SAUCE!

1443
01:00:46,275 --> 01:00:48,978
SHE STIR-FRIES OVER HIGH HEAT

1444
01:00:49,045 --> 01:00:50,346
When will you whip up the meringue?

1445
01:00:50,413 --> 01:00:52,281
Meringue? A little later.

1446
01:00:52,348 --> 01:00:56,452
4. SEASON WITH OYSTER SAUCE, SOY SAUCE,
AND GROUND PEPPER TO MAKE THE FILLING

1447
01:00:56,519 --> 01:00:58,121
The ingredients are flying out of the pan.

1448
01:00:58,187 --> 01:01:02,191
Chef Eun-yeong works on the pan
as she tastes her food.

1449
01:01:03,726 --> 01:01:05,928
-Chef Yeon-bok seems composed.
-Yes.

1450
01:01:05,995 --> 01:01:08,431
I feel so uneasy,
but why is he at such ease?

1451
01:01:08,498 --> 01:01:11,634
He'll lose a minute soon too.

1452
01:01:11,701 --> 01:01:13,102
He's chopping up cabbage.

1453
01:01:13,169 --> 01:01:14,804
He's chopping lettuce, actually.

1454
01:01:14,871 --> 01:01:16,305
-Lettuce?
-Lettuce?

1455
01:01:16,372 --> 01:01:19,242
That's lettuce.
He's still preparing ingredients.

1456
01:01:19,308 --> 01:01:21,811
Is he serving his food already?

1457
01:01:21,878 --> 01:01:23,079
He said he'd stir-fry it.

1458
01:01:23,146 --> 01:01:25,114
-It's been five minutes.
-Yes.

1459
01:01:25,181 --> 01:01:26,182
You have ten minutes left.

1460
01:01:27,717 --> 01:01:30,153
CUTTING GREEN ONION INTO BIG PIECES

1461
01:01:31,254 --> 01:01:32,955
GREEN ONION OIL

1462
01:01:33,523 --> 01:01:36,926
CHEF YEON-BOK POURS SOY SAUCE
AND FINISHES PREPARING!

1463
01:01:37,760 --> 01:01:40,196
THEIR BATTLE IS NOW IN THE MIDDLE PHASE

1464
01:01:41,130 --> 01:01:42,231
SHE HAS EGGS IN HER HANDS

1465
01:01:42,298 --> 01:01:43,766
She's about to make meringue.

1466
01:01:43,833 --> 01:01:45,601
She'll make meringue.

1467
01:01:45,668 --> 01:01:48,638
She needs to have
powerful wrists to do this.

1468
01:01:48,705 --> 01:01:52,542
Chef Eun-yeong throws in
only egg whites to make meringue.

1469
01:01:53,076 --> 01:01:55,445
It's hard to make meringue
with four egg whites.

1470
01:01:55,511 --> 01:01:58,581
-Even Kyun…
-I had a tough time with two eggs.

1471
01:01:58,648 --> 01:02:01,918
-Kyun had a tough time and almost gave up.
-It'll take a while to beat four.

1472
01:02:01,984 --> 01:02:03,386
It'll be really hard to do with four.

1473
01:02:03,453 --> 01:02:05,421
CAN SHE MAKE MERINGUE WITH 4 EGGS?

1474
01:02:07,290 --> 01:02:09,625
ROOKIE, YOU'LL GET ATTENTION
BY MAKING MERINGUE?

1475
01:02:10,293 --> 01:02:11,928
I'LL FIGHT BACK WITH A FIRE SHOW!

1476
01:02:13,262 --> 01:02:17,233
3. STIR-FRY VEGETABLES, OCTOPUS, SHRIMP
IN SOY SAUCE AND GREEN ONION OIL

1477
01:02:17,300 --> 01:02:18,234
Gosh.

1478
01:02:19,168 --> 01:02:20,636
(CASUALLY)

1479
01:02:20,703 --> 01:02:23,439
I HAVE TO GET THE FIRE SHOW

1480
01:02:24,006 --> 01:02:26,075
-Joong-ki is recording a video.
-Yes.

1481
01:02:26,142 --> 01:02:29,245
And that meringue has no sugar,
so it's even harder.

1482
01:02:29,312 --> 01:02:32,081
-Does it help with sugar?
-It does.

1483
01:02:32,148 --> 01:02:34,083
Can we implement the UNICHEF?

1484
01:02:34,150 --> 01:02:35,118
No.

1485
01:02:35,184 --> 01:02:37,787
-No.
-No, I would've called for help too.

1486
01:02:37,854 --> 01:02:39,822
I'll use this instead of the minute.

1487
01:02:39,889 --> 01:02:42,024
-Instead of the minute?
-Yes.

1488
01:02:42,091 --> 01:02:44,427
You should ask Chef Yeon-bok.

1489
01:02:44,494 --> 01:02:46,863
Chef Yeon-bok, is that okay?

1490
01:02:46,929 --> 01:02:48,598
-I should let her do it.
-Okay.

1491
01:02:48,664 --> 01:02:50,933
He'll get the minute back too.

1492
01:02:51,000 --> 01:02:52,602
Thank you, Master Lee.

1493
01:02:52,668 --> 01:02:54,003
-Help.
-Okay.

1494
01:02:54,070 --> 01:02:55,304
KWON SUNG-JUN IS THE UNICHEF!

1495
01:02:56,439 --> 01:02:58,074
You can't stop him for a minute now.

1496
01:02:58,141 --> 01:03:01,277
THE CLASS OF THE WINNER
OF CULINARY CLASS WARS

1497
01:03:02,145 --> 01:03:03,379
Sung-jun, hurry up.

1498
01:03:03,446 --> 01:03:05,982
He's good at making meringue.

1499
01:03:06,549 --> 01:03:07,984
THE EGGS BEGAN TO FOAM UP

1500
01:03:08,050 --> 01:03:09,285
-It's foaming.
-Who else?

1501
01:03:09,886 --> 01:03:11,053
TAG!

1502
01:03:11,120 --> 01:03:13,656
They're taking turns to make the meringue!

1503
01:03:13,723 --> 01:03:15,625
How thick does it have to be?

1504
01:03:15,691 --> 01:03:18,060
Completely.
It can't fall when you flip it.

1505
01:03:18,127 --> 01:03:19,695
This team has good teamwork.

1506
01:03:19,762 --> 01:03:22,498
-The UNICHEF seems a bit too frivolous.
-Yes.

1507
01:03:22,565 --> 01:03:23,499
Next, please.

1508
01:03:23,566 --> 01:03:24,801
Will Choi Kang-rok do it?

1509
01:03:24,867 --> 01:03:26,235
THE NEXT CHEF GETS UP FEELING CONSCIOUS

1510
01:03:26,302 --> 01:03:27,570
Will Choi Kang-rok do it?

1511
01:03:27,637 --> 01:03:29,472
He should. Come on.

1512
01:03:29,539 --> 01:03:31,007
Gosh, I don't have much power.

1513
01:03:31,073 --> 01:03:33,409
-He comes in.
-Choi Kang-rok makes meringue.

1514
01:03:33,476 --> 01:03:35,845
-They take turns.
-How is he that fast?

1515
01:03:35,912 --> 01:03:38,581
They all have different styles.

1516
01:03:38,648 --> 01:03:39,949
-She gave up her one-minute stop.
-It's almost done.

1517
01:03:40,016 --> 01:03:41,350
-I think it's done.
-Yes.

1518
01:03:41,918 --> 01:03:44,554
-This much? More?
-Okay.

1519
01:03:44,620 --> 01:03:46,689
-A little more.
-The three of them.

1520
01:03:47,356 --> 01:03:50,126
It's not done yet, Kang-rok.
What are you saying?

1521
01:03:50,193 --> 01:03:51,494
If you're tired, I'll take it.

1522
01:03:51,561 --> 01:03:53,095
Kang-rok makes meringue.

1523
01:03:53,162 --> 01:03:55,298
-He's about to collapse.
-Gosh.

1524
01:03:55,364 --> 01:03:56,866
A little more?

1525
01:03:56,933 --> 01:03:58,267
That's good.

1526
01:03:58,334 --> 01:03:59,468
Lao Gan Ma.

1527
01:03:59,535 --> 01:04:02,371
CHEF PARK EUN-YEONG'S
DONGPO PORK MERINGUE DUMPLINGS

1528
01:04:02,438 --> 01:04:05,274
5. MAKE MERINGUE WITH EGG WHITES,
ADD STARCH TO MAKE BATTER

1529
01:04:05,341 --> 01:04:07,643
-She's using the meringue.
-Lao Gan Ma.

1530
01:04:07,710 --> 01:04:10,079
-He uses Lao Gan Ma.
-She puts that on the meringue.

1531
01:04:10,146 --> 01:04:11,113
That looks good.

1532
01:04:11,180 --> 01:04:13,482
-Gosh.
-It's in the meringue?

1533
01:04:13,549 --> 01:04:15,017
Can it go inside?

1534
01:04:15,084 --> 01:04:18,054
-Can it come together?
-Yes, I'm starting to wonder.

1535
01:04:18,120 --> 01:04:19,989
-She adds the filling.
-I think it'll fall out right away.

1536
01:04:20,056 --> 01:04:23,926
If you deep-fry egg whites,
it'll feel rather tough.

1537
01:04:23,993 --> 01:04:26,095
-Will she deep-fry it, then?
-Yes.

1538
01:04:26,162 --> 01:04:27,029
Like that?

1539
01:04:27,096 --> 01:04:28,898
She didn't make separate dumpling skins.

1540
01:04:28,965 --> 01:04:31,234
What if the fillings pop out?

1541
01:04:31,300 --> 01:04:32,635
Then, she's done.

1542
01:04:32,702 --> 01:04:34,470
Then, she has ruined her dish.

1543
01:04:34,537 --> 01:04:35,738
-The meringue can pop.
-Yes.

1544
01:04:35,805 --> 01:04:37,173
It looks pretty firm…

1545
01:04:37,240 --> 01:04:38,341
DROPPED INTO THE OIL!

1546
01:04:38,407 --> 01:04:41,110
It looks pretty firm…

1547
01:04:41,177 --> 01:04:42,979
It's floating on the oil.

1548
01:04:43,045 --> 01:04:44,146
It's not falling out.

1549
01:04:44,213 --> 01:04:45,414
No, the fillings are staying in.

1550
01:04:45,481 --> 01:04:47,683
-How did she do that?
-Is that being deep-fried?

1551
01:04:47,750 --> 01:04:50,620
SHOWERING IT GENTLY WITH OIL

1552
01:04:50,686 --> 01:04:53,289
-Chef Eun-yeong.
-This is amazing.

1553
01:04:53,356 --> 01:04:54,924
-That's pretty nice.
-The technical Park Eun-yeong.

1554
01:04:54,991 --> 01:04:57,560
-I'll use that again later.
-You'll plagiarize again?

1555
01:04:57,627 --> 01:05:00,563
-Copying.
-I'll use it the same way.

1556
01:05:00,630 --> 01:05:02,398
The young Chinese chef.

1557
01:05:02,465 --> 01:05:03,666
-That's amazing.
-That's crazy.

1558
01:05:03,733 --> 01:05:07,203
The young Chinese chef is
putting up a good fight.

1559
01:05:07,270 --> 01:05:09,705
How will Chef Yeon-bok do?

1560
01:05:09,772 --> 01:05:12,141
Will he do a good job at stopping her?

1561
01:05:12,208 --> 01:05:13,442
Goodness.

1562
01:05:13,509 --> 01:05:15,645
LEE YEON-BOK MAKES GREEN ONION OIL TOO

1563
01:05:16,479 --> 01:05:18,281
HE ALSO ADDS WATER!

1564
01:05:18,347 --> 01:05:20,483
What's he getting now? We saw that before.

1565
01:05:20,549 --> 01:05:22,885
-Lao Gan Ma.
-Lao Gan Ma.

1566
01:05:22,952 --> 01:05:25,054
Is that doenjang or what?

1567
01:05:25,121 --> 01:05:26,555
-Doenjang?
-Peanut butter.

1568
01:05:26,622 --> 01:05:28,357
It's peanut butter!

1569
01:05:28,424 --> 01:05:31,527
He's making sauce
with peanut butter and Lao Gan Ma.

1570
01:05:31,594 --> 01:05:33,562
He made it
with peanut butter and Lao Gan Ma?

1571
01:05:33,629 --> 01:05:35,698
-I can't imagine that.
-Gosh.

1572
01:05:35,765 --> 01:05:37,900
THE OCTOPUS, SHRIMP AND VEGGIES
HE STIR-FRIED BEFORE

1573
01:05:40,736 --> 01:05:42,872
THE SEAFOOD AND VEGETABLE STIR-FRY IS DONE

1574
01:05:42,939 --> 01:05:44,774
NEXT, BRAISED NAPA CABBAGE AND TOFU

1575
01:05:44,840 --> 01:05:46,208
PICKLED GREEN ONION

1576
01:05:46,275 --> 01:05:48,978
He's putting in the juice
from pickled green onion.

1577
01:05:49,045 --> 01:05:51,814
-I see. He likes that pickle.
-Yes.

1578
01:05:51,881 --> 01:05:54,250
-It has to be delicious.
-Right?

1579
01:05:54,951 --> 01:05:56,852
That's going to become the sauce.

1580
01:05:58,321 --> 01:06:00,122
STRAINING GREEN ONION AND GARLIC

1581
01:06:00,189 --> 01:06:02,491
PUTTING THE VEGETABLE BROTH IN A NEW POT

1582
01:06:02,558 --> 01:06:03,626
They have five minutes.

1583
01:06:03,693 --> 01:06:05,962
-Five minutes!
-We have about five minutes.

1584
01:06:06,028 --> 01:06:08,698
-Jung-hwan, please go out to the field.
-Okay.

1585
01:06:09,265 --> 01:06:11,200
INTO THE LATTER HALF!

1586
01:06:11,267 --> 01:06:13,736
9. BOIL SALT, OYSTER SAUCE, GROUND PEPPER,
AND BAY LEAVES TO MAKE SAUCE

1587
01:06:13,803 --> 01:06:15,604
We have about five minutes left.

1588
01:06:15,671 --> 01:06:18,374
-Jung-hwan, please go out to the field.
-Okay.

1589
01:06:18,441 --> 01:06:20,343
This meringue got deep-fried like this.

1590
01:06:20,910 --> 01:06:22,278
-It's a wonder.
-It's a wonder.

1591
01:06:22,345 --> 01:06:24,213
Isn't the oil too hot? Flip it over.

1592
01:06:24,780 --> 01:06:25,648
TURNING

1593
01:06:25,715 --> 01:06:27,550
That looks amazing.

1594
01:06:27,616 --> 01:06:30,252
I wonder how that will turn out.

1595
01:06:30,820 --> 01:06:32,922
LEE YEON-BOK QUIETLY SPEEDS UP

1596
01:06:33,756 --> 01:06:38,861
Chef Yeon-bok just made sauce.
That one right there.

1597
01:06:38,928 --> 01:06:39,929
What's this sauce?

1598
01:06:39,996 --> 01:06:41,364
-It's for napa cabbage.
-Napa cabbage sauce.

1599
01:06:41,430 --> 01:06:43,132
I wonder how it'll taste.

1600
01:06:43,199 --> 01:06:44,233
It has to be good.

1601
01:06:44,300 --> 01:06:46,068
Will people line up for this?

1602
01:06:46,135 --> 01:06:48,137
How's the braised napa cabbage sauce?

1603
01:06:48,204 --> 01:06:50,239
So? How is it?

1604
01:06:50,306 --> 01:06:51,974
So? How is it?

1605
01:06:52,041 --> 01:06:53,275
WILL PEOPLE LINE UP?

1606
01:06:54,710 --> 01:06:58,314
-At least 20 people would line up.
-About 20.

1607
01:06:58,381 --> 01:06:59,382
Twenty would line up for that.

1608
01:06:59,448 --> 01:07:02,651
It tastes very fresh,
and I love the capsicum smell. It's fresh.

1609
01:07:02,718 --> 01:07:03,986
It must've been okay.

1610
01:07:04,053 --> 01:07:07,123
It tastes like yuringi sauce too.

1611
01:07:07,189 --> 01:07:09,759
-Hey.
-Is the tofu okay?

1612
01:07:09,825 --> 01:07:11,594
-Hey.
-Is the tofu all right?

1613
01:07:11,660 --> 01:07:14,864
-The tofu didn't get mushy.
-It didn't get mushy.

1614
01:07:14,930 --> 01:07:15,998
It looks so pretty.

1615
01:07:16,065 --> 01:07:18,801
The tofu didn't get mushy.
That's the braised napa cabbage.

1616
01:07:18,868 --> 01:07:20,569
I guess he'll pour sauce over that.

1617
01:07:22,038 --> 01:07:24,707
-Is this sauce for this dish?
-Yes.

1618
01:07:24,774 --> 01:07:27,243
-The napa cabbage.
-And he takes the cabbage.

1619
01:07:27,309 --> 01:07:29,145
-He cuts it up.
-Yes.

1620
01:07:30,212 --> 01:07:31,781
Braised napa cabbage is great.

1621
01:07:31,847 --> 01:07:33,549
6. CHOP CABBAGE INTO BITE SIZES
AND TOP IT WITH SAUCE

1622
01:07:33,616 --> 01:07:34,884
It looks great.

1623
01:07:37,453 --> 01:07:39,722
BRAISED NAPA CABBAGE AND TOFU, FINISHED

1624
01:07:41,957 --> 01:07:43,859
That looks amazing.

1625
01:07:43,926 --> 01:07:46,262
PARK EUN-YEONG SCOOPS
THE FRIED MERINGUE OUT

1626
01:07:46,762 --> 01:07:48,364
IT GOES BACK INTO THE SAUCE

1627
01:07:48,431 --> 01:07:50,099
What are you braising
the fried meringue in?

1628
01:07:50,166 --> 01:07:52,268
I made sauce
that tastes like Dongpo pork sauce.

1629
01:07:52,334 --> 01:07:54,070
This sauce is similar
to Dongpo pork sauce?

1630
01:07:54,136 --> 01:07:56,105
I'm boiling it down in soy sauce.

1631
01:07:56,172 --> 01:07:58,007
Can you get a taste
of the Dongpo pork sauce?

1632
01:07:58,074 --> 01:07:59,708
But it's boiling hot.

1633
01:07:59,775 --> 01:08:00,976
Exactly.

1634
01:08:01,043 --> 01:08:02,211
You went out to do that!

1635
01:08:02,278 --> 01:08:04,413
You're there, so you have to try it.

1636
01:08:04,480 --> 01:08:05,581
Try it now!

1637
01:08:05,648 --> 01:08:06,482
Fine.

1638
01:08:06,549 --> 01:08:07,550
GETS A NEW SPOON

1639
01:08:07,616 --> 01:08:09,652
You have three minutes.

1640
01:08:09,718 --> 01:08:11,187
Chef Eun-yeong had a taste too.

1641
01:08:11,253 --> 01:08:13,756
I've had Dongpo pork,
so I know what the sauce tastes like.

1642
01:08:13,823 --> 01:08:15,791
I'll taste it and see how similar it is.

1643
01:08:15,858 --> 01:08:17,760
-How similar is it?
-It does seem hot.

1644
01:08:17,827 --> 01:08:19,328
It's boiling rapidly.

1645
01:08:19,395 --> 01:08:21,497
Will it taste like Dongpo pork?

1646
01:08:22,598 --> 01:08:24,133
All right.

1647
01:08:24,200 --> 01:08:25,468
-Okay.
-Wait!

1648
01:08:25,534 --> 01:08:27,169
Hurry up! We're losing time!

1649
01:08:27,736 --> 01:08:30,606
Is it Dongpo pork? Or is it Dingpo pork?

1650
01:08:30,673 --> 01:08:32,808
DOES IT TASTE LIKE DONGPO PORK?

1651
01:08:32,875 --> 01:08:34,944
It still tastes like not-so-Dongpo pork.

1652
01:08:36,112 --> 01:08:38,080
-It's too bland.
-Is it?

1653
01:08:38,147 --> 01:08:39,748
-It's too bland.
-It is?

1654
01:08:39,815 --> 01:08:40,916
That's not good.

1655
01:08:40,983 --> 01:08:43,486
-I personally find it bland.
-It's bland?

1656
01:08:43,552 --> 01:08:45,121
Did she do that for Hee-jun?

1657
01:08:45,187 --> 01:08:47,089
Yes, I prefer the bland taste.

1658
01:08:47,156 --> 01:08:48,624
-I see.
-In my opinion…

1659
01:08:48,691 --> 01:08:49,792
It must've been quiet bland.

1660
01:08:49,859 --> 01:08:51,460
-It's way too bland.
-I see.

1661
01:08:53,529 --> 01:08:54,997
THE FILLING SHE MADE

1662
01:08:55,064 --> 01:08:56,899
GOES IN THE BOTTOM OF THE BOWL

1663
01:08:56,966 --> 01:08:59,201
THE MERINGUE DUMPLING

1664
01:09:00,636 --> 01:09:02,605
LANDING

1665
01:09:02,671 --> 01:09:07,276
BAY LEAF OUT, STARCH WATER IN

1666
01:09:07,343 --> 01:09:09,011
SOYA NOODLES POP OUT

1667
01:09:09,945 --> 01:09:11,547
CUT THE BAG

1668
01:09:11,614 --> 01:09:13,149
THEN DRAIN, AND IT'S OVER

1669
01:09:13,215 --> 01:09:15,184
I personally find it bland.

1670
01:09:15,251 --> 01:09:17,553
-Jung-hwan! Do you see the noodles?
-Yes?

1671
01:09:17,620 --> 01:09:18,554
Where? Yes, the stir-fried noodles.

1672
01:09:18,621 --> 01:09:20,656
Can you taste the sauce?

1673
01:09:20,723 --> 01:09:22,625
-It became dandan noodles.
-It's like art.

1674
01:09:22,691 --> 01:09:25,127
Why do you keep telling me
to only eat scorching hot food?

1675
01:09:25,194 --> 01:09:26,562
You have to try that in a hurry!

1676
01:09:26,629 --> 01:09:28,831
-It's too hot.
-We're running out of time!

1677
01:09:28,898 --> 01:09:31,033
Yes, that's it. Swallow!

1678
01:09:31,100 --> 01:09:32,601
What does it taste like?

1679
01:09:33,269 --> 01:09:35,638
What does it taste like? What's wrong?

1680
01:09:35,704 --> 01:09:37,239
The peanut butter is amazing.

1681
01:09:39,341 --> 01:09:40,676
I see.

1682
01:09:40,743 --> 01:09:42,578
-What a relief.
-But I'm not sure

1683
01:09:42,645 --> 01:09:46,415
if Hee-jun will like
the smell of Lao Gan Ma.

1684
01:09:47,883 --> 01:09:49,919
-It's only slight.
-It's slight.

1685
01:09:49,985 --> 01:09:51,053
A bit spicy.

1686
01:09:51,120 --> 01:09:53,656
I like it, but I'm not sure if he will.

1687
01:09:53,722 --> 01:09:58,027
He poured it over the lettuce,
then he'll also top it with seafood.

1688
01:09:58,093 --> 01:09:59,128
You have one minute left.

1689
01:09:59,195 --> 01:10:01,363
You have under a minute.

1690
01:10:01,430 --> 01:10:03,432
What's not working?

1691
01:10:03,499 --> 01:10:04,633
I'm all done.

1692
01:10:04,700 --> 01:10:06,202
Take your time.

1693
01:10:06,268 --> 01:10:07,603
Gosh, it looks so hot.

1694
01:10:08,437 --> 01:10:09,838
She poured the hot sauce over it.

1695
01:10:09,905 --> 01:10:12,174
Dongpo Pork Meringue Dumplings.

1696
01:10:12,241 --> 01:10:14,109
That's amazing.

1697
01:10:14,176 --> 01:10:15,778
LEE YEON-BOK GETS SEAFOOD STIR-FRY

1698
01:10:15,844 --> 01:10:18,013
AND TOPS IT ON THE DANDAN NOODLES

1699
01:10:18,080 --> 01:10:20,783
9. PUT THE SEAFOOD VEGGIE STIR-FRY
AND DANDAN NOODLES TOGETHER

1700
01:10:20,849 --> 01:10:22,017
I think it's inside.

1701
01:10:22,518 --> 01:10:25,354
-He's done!
-Chef Yeon-bok is done!

1702
01:10:25,421 --> 01:10:27,957
-He has 25 seconds left.
-Are you done?

1703
01:10:28,023 --> 01:10:29,091
EUN-YEONG BEGINS TO CHOP

1704
01:10:29,158 --> 01:10:31,327
What are you doing?
You have no time. 20 seconds.

1705
01:10:31,393 --> 01:10:33,829
-You have enough time.
-Twenty seconds!

1706
01:10:33,896 --> 01:10:34,730
Okay.

1707
01:10:34,797 --> 01:10:35,965
And fifteen seconds.

1708
01:10:36,031 --> 01:10:36,899
Are you missing anything?

1709
01:10:36,966 --> 01:10:38,601
I just need to clean this.

1710
01:10:38,667 --> 01:10:40,169
-I'm done.
-Park Eun-yeong's hands tremble.

1711
01:10:40,236 --> 01:10:42,671
-Ten seconds. Nine. Eight.
-Take your time.

1712
01:10:42,738 --> 01:10:44,273
-Seven.
-Seven.

1713
01:10:44,340 --> 01:10:46,175
-Six. Five.
-Six. Five.

1714
01:10:46,242 --> 01:10:48,611
-Four. Three.
-Four. Three.

1715
01:10:48,677 --> 01:10:50,412
-Two. One.
-Two. One.

1716
01:10:50,479 --> 01:10:53,115
PARK EUN-YEONG'S
DONGPO PORK MERINGUE DUMPLING IS DONE

1717
01:10:55,451 --> 01:10:57,152
Master Lee, I almost died.

1718
01:10:57,219 --> 01:10:58,120
Did you burn your hand?

1719
01:10:58,187 --> 01:11:00,589
I grabbed the pan,
so I got a little burned.

1720
01:11:00,656 --> 01:11:01,824
You should be careful.

1721
01:11:01,890 --> 01:11:03,559
MY RIVAL PUPIL IS ALSO MY JUNIOR CHEF

1722
01:11:03,626 --> 01:11:05,361
THEY COOKED FIERCELY FOR 15 MINUTES

1723
01:11:05,427 --> 01:11:08,197
When did you make this? My gosh.

1724
01:11:08,931 --> 01:11:11,200
When did he do that?

1725
01:11:11,267 --> 01:11:13,002
I'M GETTING THIRSTY

1726
01:11:13,068 --> 01:11:14,436
Gosh, this is harsh.

1727
01:11:14,503 --> 01:11:15,904
Man, I'm in so much trouble.

1728
01:11:15,971 --> 01:11:16,972
THE NEXT UP IS PANICKING

1729
01:11:17,473 --> 01:11:21,310
-These look amazing.
-It was so dramatic.

1730
01:11:21,944 --> 01:11:23,812
I made stir-fry noodles
with peanut butter,

1731
01:11:23,879 --> 01:11:26,315
then topped it
with seafood and vegetable stir-fry.

1732
01:11:27,149 --> 01:11:28,651
And that's braised napa cabbage.

1733
01:11:28,717 --> 01:11:30,386
BRAISED NAPA CABBAGE
TO HUMOR HEE-JUN'S TASTE

1734
01:11:31,020 --> 01:11:33,088
It smells so good. It looks great.

1735
01:11:33,155 --> 01:11:35,057
CHEF LEE YEON-BOK'S YNF

1736
01:11:35,124 --> 01:11:36,692
It looks great.

1737
01:11:36,759 --> 01:11:40,629
Hee-jun said he didn't enjoy Chinese food
as they were a bit strong for his taste.

1738
01:11:40,696 --> 01:11:44,433
You'll get to taste
the flavors you usually don't eat.

1739
01:11:45,067 --> 01:11:46,468
I've never had a dish

1740
01:11:46,535 --> 01:11:48,003
-made with peanut butter.
-Right?

1741
01:11:48,070 --> 01:11:51,507
He only eats peanut butter
when he has to put on weight.

1742
01:11:51,573 --> 01:11:53,242
And the noodles aren't made with flour.

1743
01:11:53,842 --> 01:11:55,144
Those are soya noodles.

1744
01:11:55,844 --> 01:11:56,979
Soya noodles.

1745
01:11:57,046 --> 01:11:59,014
He's savoring the flavor.

1746
01:11:59,782 --> 01:12:00,616
The seafood…

1747
01:12:00,683 --> 01:12:02,418
Whoa, it's spicy.

1748
01:12:02,484 --> 01:12:03,952
It must've hit him hard.

1749
01:12:04,019 --> 01:12:05,487
SHAKING IN FEAR, I-IT'S SPICY?

1750
01:12:05,554 --> 01:12:07,222
He didn't like food
that tastes too strong.

1751
01:12:07,289 --> 01:12:10,459
Does Lao Gan Ma have that spicy taste?

1752
01:12:10,526 --> 01:12:12,328
Yes, it tastes spicy.

1753
01:12:12,394 --> 01:12:14,263
Jung-hwan pointed that out.

1754
01:12:14,330 --> 01:12:15,464
That it has a bit of a kick.

1755
01:12:15,531 --> 01:12:18,534
He tasted it
after I already put the sauce in.

1756
01:12:19,535 --> 01:12:23,072
WE'VE NEVER SEEN LEE YEON-BOK LIKE THIS

1757
01:12:24,573 --> 01:12:26,375
But it's not spicy at all
with the veggies.

1758
01:12:26,442 --> 01:12:28,310
-Is it okay?
-Yes, it's all right.

1759
01:12:28,377 --> 01:12:29,745
-But it does make me cough.
-Cough?

1760
01:12:30,379 --> 01:12:31,380
It does make him cough.

1761
01:12:31,447 --> 01:12:32,548
OCTOPUS

1762
01:12:33,449 --> 01:12:35,517
-Did you put the octopus in here too?
-Yes.

1763
01:12:35,584 --> 01:12:37,786
-He topped it with a piece of octopus.
-Gosh, it looks good.

1764
01:12:37,853 --> 01:12:39,722
-How's the octopus?
-You'll feel that texture.

1765
01:12:39,788 --> 01:12:41,824
The octopus tastes really good.

1766
01:12:41,890 --> 01:12:44,593
It shouldn't be too tough.

1767
01:12:44,660 --> 01:12:48,197
But I find it a little unfamiliar

1768
01:12:48,263 --> 01:12:52,434
to taste peanut butter with noodles.

1769
01:12:52,501 --> 01:12:54,136
You find it unfamiliar.

1770
01:12:54,203 --> 01:12:55,671
But you like peanut butter.

1771
01:12:55,738 --> 01:12:57,706
I do, but I eat it on bread.

1772
01:12:57,773 --> 01:12:59,074
It's now in a dish.

1773
01:12:59,141 --> 01:13:01,076
-It does feel unfamiliar.
-I see.

1774
01:13:01,143 --> 01:13:03,011
-It felt strange.
-Yes.

1775
01:13:03,078 --> 01:13:04,546
Let's move on.

1776
01:13:04,613 --> 01:13:06,715
The braised napa cabbage.

1777
01:13:06,782 --> 01:13:11,520
It feels like the round is going
a bit unfavorably for Chef Yeon-bok.

1778
01:13:11,587 --> 01:13:13,889
-He still has the cabbage.
-He has the braised cabbage.

1779
01:13:14,490 --> 01:13:15,791
The braised napa cabbage.

1780
01:13:15,858 --> 01:13:17,426
The tofu didn't get mushy.

1781
01:13:17,960 --> 01:13:18,961
MMM

1782
01:13:21,063 --> 01:13:22,931
This is so good.

1783
01:13:23,899 --> 01:13:26,802
The braised napa cabbage
seems to have captured his taste buds.

1784
01:13:26,869 --> 01:13:29,004
This is what I usually like to eat,
the healthy taste.

1785
01:13:29,071 --> 01:13:33,208
Tofu, vegetables,
and this yuringi-like sauce.

1786
01:13:33,275 --> 01:13:34,309
-Doesn't it taste fresh?
-Yes.

1787
01:13:34,376 --> 01:13:37,913
I love the fresh taste
with capsicum and whatnot.

1788
01:13:37,980 --> 01:13:39,214
And the napa cabbage?

1789
01:13:39,848 --> 01:13:41,850
HE DEFINITELY LIKES HEALTHY FOOD

1790
01:13:41,917 --> 01:13:43,519
The mix of tofu and cabbage.

1791
01:13:45,487 --> 01:13:47,689
DONGPO PORK DUMPLING MADE WITH MERINGUE

1792
01:13:47,756 --> 01:13:50,759
Dongpo Pork Meringue Dumpling
by Chef Park Eun-yeong.

1793
01:13:50,826 --> 01:13:52,561
CHEF PARK EUN-YEONG'S
DONGPO PORK MERINGUE DUMPLING

1794
01:13:52,628 --> 01:13:55,330
Hee-jun had been dying to eat
some real Dongpo pork.

1795
01:13:55,397 --> 01:13:59,401
He could feel more disappointed
because he had such high expectations.

1796
01:13:59,468 --> 01:14:03,672
I made the best Dongpo pork dumpling
I can make within 15 minutes.

1797
01:14:03,739 --> 01:14:05,641
That Dongpo pork dumpling was
made only for you.

1798
01:14:05,707 --> 01:14:07,075
-Yes.
-And it's…

1799
01:14:07,142 --> 01:14:08,076
Wait.

1800
01:14:08,143 --> 01:14:09,912
Why do you sound so rushed?

1801
01:14:09,978 --> 01:14:12,147
No, I always talk fast.

1802
01:14:12,214 --> 01:14:14,983
-I talk fast.
-You're promoting your dish.

1803
01:14:15,050 --> 01:14:17,152
That Dongpo pork dumpling was
made just for you.

1804
01:14:17,219 --> 01:14:20,456
I hope you eat it with the sauce

1805
01:14:20,522 --> 01:14:23,292
and enjoy the texture of the meringue too.

1806
01:14:23,358 --> 01:14:25,794
I mean, she made meringue
and turned it into dumpling skin?

1807
01:14:25,861 --> 01:14:28,096
-I've never seen a dish like this.
-Right.

1808
01:14:28,664 --> 01:14:31,333
-It looks pretty.
-Yes, it does.

1809
01:14:31,400 --> 01:14:35,237
You can scoop up the filling
on the bottom and eat that too.

1810
01:14:35,304 --> 01:14:37,005
Gosh, it looks so new.

1811
01:14:37,072 --> 01:14:38,707
-Like that?
-Yes, like that.

1812
01:14:38,774 --> 01:14:40,142
He's taking a bite!

1813
01:14:40,209 --> 01:14:41,777
HOW IS DONGPO PORK MERINGUE DUMPLING?

1814
01:14:41,844 --> 01:14:42,845
And?

1815
01:14:44,046 --> 01:14:46,715
-The meringue dumpling.
-And?

1816
01:14:46,782 --> 01:14:48,350
We've never seen
a dish like that on this show.

1817
01:14:49,885 --> 01:14:51,053
HMM…

1818
01:14:51,587 --> 01:14:53,522
He's very careful.

1819
01:14:53,589 --> 01:14:55,891
My heart is about to drop
while watching him.

1820
01:14:55,958 --> 01:14:57,192
EXHALE…

1821
01:14:57,259 --> 01:14:59,127
My heart is about to drop too.

1822
01:14:59,194 --> 01:15:01,463
Chef Yeon-bok is going through the fridge.

1823
01:15:02,097 --> 01:15:04,099
He can't bear to listen to him.

1824
01:15:04,166 --> 01:15:08,203
-She feels frustrated and drinks water.
-She's drinking water.

1825
01:15:08,270 --> 01:15:10,239
HE'S DRINKING COLA INSTEAD

1826
01:15:10,305 --> 01:15:11,773
How's Dongpo Pork Meringue Dumpling?

1827
01:15:11,840 --> 01:15:14,376
My wife usually uses the thin pork belly

1828
01:15:14,443 --> 01:15:18,013
to whip up spicy stir-fried pork for me.

1829
01:15:18,080 --> 01:15:23,619
I never expected the pork belly
to turn out tasting like Dongpo pork.

1830
01:15:23,685 --> 01:15:24,720
It's amazing.

1831
01:15:24,786 --> 01:15:26,355
Does it taste like Dongpo pork?

1832
01:15:26,421 --> 01:15:28,757
-Yes.
-It tastes like it?

1833
01:15:28,824 --> 01:15:31,159
Well, I don't really know how it tastes.

1834
01:15:31,226 --> 01:15:32,427
He's so honest.

1835
01:15:32,494 --> 01:15:34,096
This sauce is so good.

1836
01:15:34,162 --> 01:15:37,866
How can my fridge
put something like this together?

1837
01:15:37,933 --> 01:15:42,137
I mixed green onion oil and truffle oil…

1838
01:15:42,204 --> 01:15:44,606
-Truffle oil.
-…to give you that subtle taste.

1839
01:15:44,673 --> 01:15:45,674
She's rushing.

1840
01:15:46,608 --> 01:15:48,510
I love the smell of the truffle oil.

1841
01:15:48,577 --> 01:15:50,512
Does the egg have that raw smell?

1842
01:15:50,579 --> 01:15:53,315
I'm unfamiliar
with the texture of the meringue.

1843
01:15:54,550 --> 01:15:55,851
It is pretty unfamiliar.

1844
01:15:55,918 --> 01:15:58,887
-My heart drops when he says that.
-It must.

1845
01:15:59,488 --> 01:16:01,423
HIS HEART DROPS FOR HIM

1846
01:16:01,490 --> 01:16:04,293
-But it doesn't smell raw?
-No.

1847
01:16:04,359 --> 01:16:06,929
I feel at ease to know
that it's made with egg whites.

1848
01:16:08,697 --> 01:16:11,867
Let's try Chef Yeon-bok's YNF first.

1849
01:16:11,934 --> 01:16:13,635
This peanut butter and…

1850
01:16:13,702 --> 01:16:15,837
He found this unfamiliar.

1851
01:16:16,572 --> 01:16:19,074
I wonder what everyone else will think.

1852
01:16:21,109 --> 01:16:23,245
-It's nutty.
-It's really good.

1853
01:16:24,913 --> 01:16:25,981
-Gosh.
-The sauce.

1854
01:16:27,049 --> 01:16:28,183
How is it?

1855
01:16:28,250 --> 01:16:32,654
I'm so proud
of appearing in <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

1856
01:16:32,721 --> 01:16:33,889
I see.

1857
01:16:33,956 --> 01:16:35,857
-It's so good.
-Is it?

1858
01:16:35,924 --> 01:16:39,861
The peanut butter sauce goes
so well with the noodles.

1859
01:16:39,928 --> 01:16:44,566
I can feel the spiciness toward the end,

1860
01:16:44,633 --> 01:16:46,802
but I love that.

1861
01:16:46,868 --> 01:16:49,638
He doesn't like bold flavors,

1862
01:16:49,705 --> 01:16:53,408
so it's much more subtle and milder
than actual dandan noodles.

1863
01:16:53,475 --> 01:16:56,979
The napa cabbage
still had its crunch but was fully cooked.

1864
01:16:57,045 --> 01:16:58,914
I wouldn't want meat
if I had this cabbage.

1865
01:16:58,981 --> 01:17:00,549
THE CABBAGE WAS SO GOOD
THAT HE DIDN'T MISS ANY MEAT

1866
01:17:00,616 --> 01:17:02,084
I thought the vegetables

1867
01:17:02,150 --> 01:17:06,121
that came with the noodles were
cooked to perfection.

1868
01:17:06,188 --> 01:17:08,056
-I loved that.
-I see.

1869
01:17:08,123 --> 01:17:10,592
-The cooking of the vegetables.
-It had that crunch.

1870
01:17:10,659 --> 01:17:13,228
This time, Dongpo Pork Meringue Dumpling.

1871
01:17:13,295 --> 01:17:15,831
I was so curious about the texture.

1872
01:17:15,897 --> 01:17:19,134
CHEF PARK EUN-YEONG'S
DONGPO PORK MERINGUE DUMPLING

1873
01:17:19,201 --> 01:17:21,637
It does have that meringue texture.

1874
01:17:21,703 --> 01:17:23,538
The customer…

1875
01:17:24,106 --> 01:17:24,940
Customer?

1876
01:17:25,007 --> 01:17:26,341
The customer. The fridge owner.

1877
01:17:26,408 --> 01:17:28,777
The customer's order was

1878
01:17:28,844 --> 01:17:31,980
reflected into this dish 100%.

1879
01:17:32,047 --> 01:17:35,851
It was the best dish she could make
within 15 minutes.

1880
01:17:35,917 --> 01:17:41,056
You didn't have the ingredients
to make Dongpo pork, but it had that hint.

1881
01:17:41,123 --> 01:17:43,025
You managed to create the taste
in such a short while.

1882
01:17:43,091 --> 01:17:45,060
I was a bit worried

1883
01:17:45,127 --> 01:17:49,231
because I easily spot
the taste of rawness even in boiled eggs.

1884
01:17:49,297 --> 01:17:51,366
But it's so odd that
it doesn't taste raw at all.

1885
01:17:51,933 --> 01:17:54,569
And it was a bit too bland for my taste.

1886
01:17:55,237 --> 01:17:56,638
The fillings, I mean.

1887
01:17:56,705 --> 01:18:01,143
I could feel how much you two tried
to meet my needs in the dishes.

1888
01:18:01,743 --> 01:18:03,745
-This is so hard to choose.
-Of course.

1889
01:18:03,812 --> 01:18:06,782
The Chinese cuisine industry may jolt
depending on your decision.

1890
01:18:06,848 --> 01:18:08,984
A LOT OF PRESSURE

1891
01:18:09,051 --> 01:18:13,188
This is an important battle
that can have an impact in the industry.

1892
01:18:13,255 --> 01:18:16,692
Press one for Lee Yeon-bok,
and press two for Park Eun-yeong.

1893
01:18:16,758 --> 01:18:20,028
Today was pretty much
his first day eating Chinese food.

1894
01:18:20,095 --> 01:18:21,830
CHINESE CHEFS AND A ROOKIE TO CHINESE FOOD

1895
01:18:21,897 --> 01:18:24,466
The rookie to Chinese food.

1896
01:18:24,533 --> 01:18:26,735
Who will he choose?

1897
01:18:26,802 --> 01:18:28,970
Let us find out the result.

1898
01:18:29,037 --> 01:18:30,872
-The Master of Chinese Cuisine
-This must've been hard.

1899
01:18:30,939 --> 01:18:33,575
versus the Goddess of Chinese Cuisine.

1900
01:18:33,642 --> 01:18:36,545
Who captured Hee-jun's taste?

1901
01:18:36,611 --> 01:18:39,014
Who'll take the second star?

1902
01:18:39,081 --> 01:18:41,850
Which place will people line up at?

1903
01:18:41,917 --> 01:18:43,085
Which side?

1904
01:18:45,020 --> 01:18:46,221
Which side?

1905
01:18:46,288 --> 01:18:48,290
PARK EUN-YEONG WINS

1906
01:18:48,356 --> 01:18:50,659
PARK EUN-YEONG'S
DONGPO PORK MERINGUE DUMPLING WINS

1907
01:18:50,726 --> 01:18:52,227
-Congratulations.
-Thank you.

1908
01:18:52,294 --> 01:18:54,396
Chef Eun-yeong wins!

1909
01:18:54,463 --> 01:18:57,265
-My gosh.
-She won!

1910
01:18:57,332 --> 01:19:00,302
I think a huge uproar will
overtake the industry.

1911
01:19:02,104 --> 01:19:03,472
I'm so sorry.

1912
01:19:03,538 --> 01:19:05,273
-It's fine.
-Yes.

1913
01:19:05,340 --> 01:19:08,543
The decision of the fridge owner is
absolutely theirs.

1914
01:19:08,610 --> 01:19:11,213
-Everyone has such different tastes.
-You may want to complain, but…

1915
01:19:11,279 --> 01:19:13,648
I'm still just a beginner in Chinese food,

1916
01:19:13,715 --> 01:19:17,753
so I wasn't used to the flavors
of dandan noodles.

1917
01:19:17,819 --> 01:19:20,522
I think it was easier
to enjoy Chef Eun-yeong's dish.

1918
01:19:20,589 --> 01:19:21,723
I see.

1919
01:19:21,790 --> 01:19:23,692
Chef Eun-yeong, any thoughts?

1920
01:19:23,759 --> 01:19:26,528
I want to thank the two chefs
who helped out as UNICHEF.

1921
01:19:26,595 --> 01:19:27,796
-There were three.
-Meringue…

1922
01:19:27,863 --> 01:19:31,266
Wait a minute, Chef Kang-rok protests.
Three chefs helped you.

1923
01:19:31,333 --> 01:19:33,602
-Yes, three.
-He's right.

1924
01:19:33,668 --> 01:19:35,637
All three helped you.

1925
01:19:35,704 --> 01:19:37,806
He rarely ever talks,

1926
01:19:37,873 --> 01:19:39,808
but he suddenly said, "There were three."

1927
01:19:41,176 --> 01:19:43,078
-Let's start over.
-That's right, three people.

1928
01:19:43,145 --> 01:19:46,148
I want to thank the three UNICHEF members,

1929
01:19:46,214 --> 01:19:49,384
as well as Chef Yeon-bok
for his understanding.

1930
01:19:49,451 --> 01:19:50,619
I was only chosen by him

1931
01:19:50,685 --> 01:19:53,288
because I was able to make the meringue.

1932
01:19:53,355 --> 01:19:54,289
She's right.

1933
01:19:54,356 --> 01:19:57,726
So how was it, Chef Yeon-bok?

1934
01:19:57,793 --> 01:20:00,362
Well, it was about time I retired.

1935
01:20:01,029 --> 01:20:01,963
Come on.

1936
01:20:02,030 --> 01:20:04,366
What do you mean, you'll retire?

1937
01:20:04,432 --> 01:20:06,468
He'll retire because of Hee-jun?

1938
01:20:06,535 --> 01:20:08,937
No, you can't. No.

1939
01:20:09,004 --> 01:20:10,272
The braised cabbage was excellent.

1940
01:20:10,338 --> 01:20:11,673
You're too late.

1941
01:20:11,740 --> 01:20:14,142
-Hee-jun made him retire!
-Come on!

1942
01:20:14,209 --> 01:20:15,410
I WAS JUST JOKING

1943
01:20:15,477 --> 01:20:16,611
Goodness gracious.

1944
01:20:16,678 --> 01:20:19,381
Hee-jun, please put the star on her.

1945
01:20:20,215 --> 01:20:22,651
She records her second win.
Congratulations.

1946
01:20:23,652 --> 01:20:26,188
DONGPO PORK MERINGUE DUMPLING
BY CHEF PARK EUN-YEONG

1947
01:20:26,254 --> 01:20:28,623
THE RECIPE

1948
01:20:28,690 --> 01:20:31,326
We present Joong-ki's fridge!

1949
01:20:31,393 --> 01:20:33,328
YOU HAVE SOMETHING LIKE THIS?

1950
01:20:33,395 --> 01:20:34,830
NEVER-BEFORE-SEEN INGREDIENTS?

1951
01:20:34,896 --> 01:20:36,698
I've fallen for Italian cuisine lately.

1952
01:20:36,765 --> 01:20:38,300
GLAD

1953
01:20:38,366 --> 01:20:39,935
Is your wife okay with this?

1954
01:20:40,001 --> 01:20:42,137
She told you to use everything freely.

1955
01:20:42,204 --> 01:20:44,706
This will be the first return match.

1956
01:20:44,773 --> 01:20:46,641
-I want to use it today.
-You do?

1957
01:20:46,708 --> 01:20:47,676
Do you think you can win?

1958
01:20:48,643 --> 01:20:49,578
The salsa dance?

1959
01:20:49,644 --> 01:20:51,880
He's not supposed to cross over.

1960
01:20:51,947 --> 01:20:53,281
I'm so looking forward to this.

1961
01:20:53,348 --> 01:20:55,884
Who will become the best Italian chef?

1962
01:20:55,951 --> 01:20:58,453
I'm going to win anyway.

1963
01:20:58,520 --> 01:21:00,388
A HEAD-ON BATTLE
WITH HIS 15-MINUTE RISOTTO!

1964
01:21:00,455 --> 01:21:01,623
It's impossible to do in 15 minutes.

1965
01:21:01,690 --> 01:21:04,159
Let me ask you one last time.
Will the risotto be ready?

1966
01:21:04,226 --> 01:21:05,594
Is it ready? Is it?

1967
01:21:05,660 --> 01:21:07,295
Gosh, I can't watch this.

1968
01:21:10,332 --> 01:21:11,499
He's savoring it.

1969
01:21:11,566 --> 01:21:14,069
-Mamma mia.
-Mamma mia.

1970
01:21:15,036 --> 01:21:16,104
Mamma mia!

1971
01:21:19,040 --> 01:21:20,609
He's shooting at him.

1972
01:21:21,509 --> 01:21:22,844
"You're all dead."

1973
01:21:33,955 --> 01:21:38,960
Subtitle translation by: Eunsook Youn
